Commentary: Beaten straightaway! Cummins serves it close to off stump on a good length, Burns pushes at it from the crease but the angle of the bowler beats his bat.
Better from Burns this time. An identical delivery, on and around off, angling away after pitching, Burns shoulders arms.
Poor footwork this time by Burns. Fullish and outside off, shaping away, Burns walks in with an indecisive cover drive and gets beaten comprehensively.
A touch short in length on this occasion, around off, Rory is on his toes as he taps it down in front of the gully fielder.
Straighter delivery this time, on a good length, Burns brings a straight bat down and pushes it towards wide mid on.
Left alone! On a driving length outside off, Burns covers his stumps and lets it be. Maiden to start.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Nearly a drag on! A length ball landing just outside off and shaping in with some extra bounce, Denly decides to make a leave but it takes his gloves and drops near the stumps.

Once again some visible extra bounce. Hazlewood delivers it on middle and leg, Denly is hurried up in defense. It once again hits him on the top of the bat and rolls wide of short leg. England are away with a single.
Hurls in a length ball in the zone outside off, Burns covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shortish and on middle, jumping onto the batsman who tries to defend from the crease. No bat it seems as the ball goes off the thigh pad to the off side.

FOUR! This shot will make Burns feel a lot confident about himself. Hazlewood overpitches the last delivery of the over, it's outside off and Burns confidently drives it off his front foot. The ball finds the middle of his bat and races through cover-point for a boundary.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, easy pace from Cummins, quips Bumble on air. A comfortable leave for Denly outside off.
Angles in a good length delivery on off, Denly sticks on the back foot and defends it down in front of short leg.

What a stop, Mitchell Marsh! Top work in the field, making his presence felt. Fuller in length and outside off, Denly unfurls a cracking drive through the line but Marsh at short extra cover makes a fine diving stop. Prevents a boundary and is all smiles.
Outside off, Denly has a watchful leave.

Soft hands from Joe! Cummins puts it on a fuller length and just outside off, Denly opens the face of the bat with a loose bottom hand. It finds the outer half of his blade and rolls wide of gully for a couple of runs.

A glorious straight drive but a stupendous stop in the followthrough by Cummins. Again a certain boundary is prevented. Too full in length on off, Denly drives it back with the full face of the bat but fails to get it past the bowler.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Lands it on a length and just outside off, Burns sticks on the back foot and taps it down safely on the off side.

BURNS SURVIVES! Hazlewood delivers it just ahead of a length around middle and gets it to shape back in a shade. Burns is on the back foot looking to defend but misses and takes a blow on his back leg. The Aussies appeal and umpire Erasmus agrees after giving it a thought. Burns is quick to refer it though. The Ultra Edge detects nothing and then the Ball Tracker finds it to be going over the off stump. Good use of the technology by Burns.
On middle and off, defended from the back foot by Rory.
Another back foot defense by Burns. Solid.
Lets the ball go outside his off stump. End of an eventful over.

Shout for a caught behind! Not given. Cummins bowls a big inswinger there, landing around off and nipping back in sharply. Denly tries defending but seems to have missed it. It brushes his back leg and travels straight into the gloves of Paine. The Aussie skipper appeals after collecting and Cummins also joins him. Umpire Dharmasena remains unmoved. Good decision by the Sri Lankan, confirm the replays.

FOUR! Good effort by Labuschagne but in vain. Cummins lands it on a length outside off, Denly is late in taking his bat away and it kisses the bottom edge. The ball screams away from gully and Marnus gives the chase. He puts in a dive near the fence and tries to pull it back. The replays though show that his right hand was in contact with the rope while he was doing so as the umpire signals a boundary after talking upstairs.
Denly has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Excellent delivery again. Denly has no clue about it. A length ball shaping in from a length outside off, Denly pushes at it tamely but is beaten on the inside edge.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks in time to let that one go over him.
Full and angling down the leg side, Joe tries flicking but fails to put bat on ball.
Good length delivery around off, Burns stays back-footed and defends it to the off side.
Bouncer served by Josh, Burns swayed away at the last moment.
FOUR! Nicely played. No risk at all in this shot. Fuller length delivery on middle and off, Burns just brings down a straight bat and pushes it gently down the ground for a boundary at long on.
Plenty of risk on this shot. It's a length ball on off, Burns has a push at it without much footwork and gets an inside edge past the stumps to fine leg. A single is taken.

FOUR! This is the chink in his armour. Every time Denly sees width outside off, his eyes light up. Just can't help himself there. Feels he has to go after those deliveries. Once again attempts for a booming drive through the line but ends up slicing it in the air over backward point for a boundary.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump. 9 from the over but Hazlewood did create a few chances.
In the zone outside off, Burns feels no need to play at it.

Beaten! This delivery leaves the batsman with the angle of the bowler. Since it appears to be closer to the off stump, Burns decides to have a play at it this time. But the ball keeps on leaving him and beats the outside edge of his willow.
Nice and straight from Cummins there. On middle and off, Burns covers the line and blocks it soundly on the leg side.
Deceives the batsman a bit there by bowling a bouncer. Burns is on the move for a shot, picks the length late but then does well to duck in time.
The follow up delivery from Cummins is a lovely tempter outside off. On a driving length but Burns is not walking into the trap. Makes a sensible leave.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Cummins errs in his line on this occasion. This one is served on the leg stump line and Burns neatly deflects it off his pads to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on middle, jumping in a bit, Denly is on his back foot in defense.
A leg stump line from Siddle on this occasion, Denly flicks but Wade at backward short leg does well to make a fine stop. Saves a few runs there for his team.
Too wide outside off, an easy leave this time by Denly.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, Denly has nothing to do with it as well.
Siddle keeps his line closer to the off stump by angling in a length ball, Denly defends it back safely.

An embarrassing fall for Mitchell Marsh! Short in length and outside off, Denly goes on his toes and punches it past Marsh at extra cover. The tall all-rounder gives the chase, the ball also slows down a bit, Marsh bends to pick it but then lands on his hips. Gets up quickly though and returns the ball in play. Three added to the total. This is now the highest opening stand in this Ashes for either side. Hmm... tells you how mediocre it has been from both teams!

Shout for an lbw! Not given. Back of a length ball around off and shaping back in, Denly tries to defend but misses and is hit on the back leg. They appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays find no wood. A bit similar to Burns' but no DRS involved.
Sliding down the leg side, Denly tries flicking but misses.

DROPPED, DROPPED, CAUGHT! OUT! Steven Smith eventually holds on to the catch in the third attempt. England have been dropping him but he doesn't return the favour, quips my fellow commentator. A nothing delivery to be honest. It's all Denly's fault that he goes chasing after a length ball outside off. We have talked earlier also about his inability to restrain himself. Goes for a booming drive away from his body only to get a thick outside edge behind. It travels at a nice height at second slip where Smith reacts to catch it but starts to lose his balance. The ball pops out of his hands first time but then it sticks near his chest and Steven tries to catch it on the second attempt. By now, he is already down on his knees but still fails to catch the ball. On the third attempt, Smudge finally cups it much to the delight of Pat Cummins. Joe departs soon after England posted the best opening partnership of this Ashes.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fullish and on middle, Root leans across and clips it wide of mid on for a run.
Cummins switches to 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball on middle, Burns punches it down through mid on for a couple of runs.
On a length and outside off, Root looks to defend to the off side but the ball goes off the inside edge and hits him on the pads before going towards point.
Good length and around off, Root defends it towards point.
FOUR! That should ease some nerves for the English skipper. Siddle bowls on a length but offers width and Root obliges. He goes back and cuts it over backward point for a boundary.
Beaten! Root is in two minds as he prods forward to this length ball. Luckily for him the ball goes past the outside edge.
Root defends this length delivery towards the off side.
FOUR! You just can't offer width to this man. Siddle once again makes the mistake of offering the width and Root once again carves him over the backward point region for a boundary.
Bouncer! Hazlewood goes short and Burns is happy to let that pass over him.
On a length and outside off, Burns looks to drive it through the off side but fails to lay bat on ball.
On a fuller length and outside off, Burns defends it off his back foot toward the off side.
Hazlewood overpitches and serves one up on his pads, Burns flicks it through the mid-wicket region and the batsmen cross over for three.
Root defends this length delivery outside off towards covers off his back foot.
Fuller one on the pads, Root flicks it to mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
On an length and outside off, Root looks to run it down to third man but ends up playing it to point.
BEATEN! Rare false shot from Root. Width on offer on this length ball, Root looks to cut it but is nowhere near the line of the delivery.

Shot! But not in the gap! Short in length and around off, Root looks to pull but the ball goes off the toe end of his bat. Mitchell Marsh at short mid-wicket hobbles to his right and ensures that no run is taken.
Length ball outside off, Root drives it through covers off the back foot and the batsmen cross for three.

FOUR! MISFIELD! Burns looks to run this length delivery down to third man.  The man at gully dives but fails to gather the ball. It goes past him towards the third man fence and Labuschagne gives the chase from the slips. He tries pulling it near the fence but fails in his effort. His shoulders get stuck inside the boundary line but luckily he has not hurt himself.
Burns looks to defend this length ball outside off but gets a soft leading edge which falls short of the third slip.
Angles in a length ball on off, Root covers the line and pushes it out to extra cover.
Angling in on a fuller length around off, Joe is solidly behind the line in defense.
Keeps it on and around off, a length ball, Root defends it off his back foot.
Shortish and on top of off stump, Root is on his toes as he taps it down to gully.
Some movement in the air, fuller and on off, Root brings down a straight bat in defense.
Nearly goes through! Fullish and on off, moving back in, Root goes hard at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It then rolls behind towards the slip cordon.
Fullish ball outside off to start after the Drinks break by Marsh. Burns pushes this towards cover.
Good length ball outside off, Burns leaves this alone.
Another good length ball, this time closer to the off pole. Burns pushes this off the back foot towards mid off.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg and gives the strike to his skipper Joe Root.
Good running! Ahead of a good length, Root pushes this towards extra cover with soft hands and takes a quick single. Keeping the visitors on their toes.
Just outside off, Burns pushes this towards cover.
Length ball on the hips of Root, he tucks it towards the leg side.
Good movement for Hazlewood here. He pitches this a bit outside off, it nips back in. Root shoulders arms to it and Paine dives to his left as he catches it with one hand.
Length ball outside off, Root pushes this towards point.
Again near the hips of Root, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball just outside off, Root tries to cut it but it goes off the inside half towards the slip cordon on the bounce.
Gentle loosener. Down the leg side by Marsh to start off, Burns leaves it alone.
Again on the leg side, Burns tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Good running again! Fullish outside off, Root plays it with soft hands towards cover-point and takes a quick single.
Way too wide outside off, Burns leaves it alone.
FOUR! Great shot by Burns this. This is full and just around off, Burns gets on the front foot and drives this one through mid on for a boundary.
Just outside off, the ball has taken the inside edge of the bat and thuds into the pads.
Outside off, left alone by Root.
Length ball just outside off, Root pushes it towards the man at point.
Another length ball outside off, Root opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third man region for a single.
Bouncer by Cummins to Burns, he picks it up in time and ducks under it.
Another bouncer, this one is outside off, Burns sways away from it easily.
Length ball wide outside off, Burns defends this towards the man at point.
Fullish and shaping in, Root looks to block it out but gets an inside edge on it and the ball then goes onto hit the pads.
Length ball outside off, Root cuts this one through cover-point. The fielder hares after it and stops it before reaching the fence. The batters take three in the meantime.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Burns defends it from within the crease.
Good length ball outside off, Burns pushes this back towards the bowler.
Burns has defended it from within the crease onto the pitch.
Cummins dishes out a length ball, Root does well to block it out.
Good ball by Cummins, he bowls it on a length and just around off. It nips back in after pitching and cuts Root into half in his attempted defense as the ball sneaks between the bat and his body.
Another jaffa! This one is pitched again on a length but this time it moves away. Root looks to play at it but takes his bat away from the line of the delivery at the last moment.
Down the leg side to follow up two very good deliveries, Root tries to flick but misses.
Full and wide outside off, Root cuts this one through cover-point. The batters take three.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a couple.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Root, he tries to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Another one on the pads, this time Burns tries to block it but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, fullish ball. Burns shuffles across and tries to flick it towards mid-wicket. It goes off the inner half of his bat towards square leg. It's in the gap and the batters take two.
Burns has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Beaten! Length ball just around off, Burns looks to defend but is beaten.
Jaffa by Cummins! He bowls this on a length and outside off, it moves a shade away and misses the outside edge of Root's bat by a whisker.

DROPPED! What has Siddle done here? This was a dolly and he has put it down! Short ball by Cummins on the off pole line, Root pulls it uppishly towards fine leg off the top edge. Siddle is stationed there and the ball goes to the right of him. He runs across, stretches both his hands out but it bursts through. It's almost chest height but the ball pops out of his hands and slips onto the ground. The batters take one and the English skipper survives. Costly miss.
Bouncer this time on the off pole line, Burns ducks under it.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns takes a late call of leaving it and bottom edges it behind near the slip cordon.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards fine leg and the batters take three.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Just outside off, Root guides it straight towards third man.

50-run stand up between Root and Burns! On the leg stump line, Root looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. It rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye. A much-needed partnership for England here.
Fullish ball outside off, Burns pushes this towards cover and takes a couple.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
On the pads of Burns, he tucks it towards the leg side.
Root chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

DROPPED AGAIN! Lucky day for the English skipper here! Peach of a delivery from Cummins. He bowls this one on a back of a length and just outside off, getting it to nip away with some extra bounce. Root plays at it after going onto his toes but gets a thick outside edge on it. It's going almost straight towards Warner at first slip but Paine intervenes with a leap to his right. He tries to take it with one hand but puts it down. Had he left it for Warner, he might have taken it with ease as it was looking a much easier catch for David. Root is hanging on by the skin of his teeth here and the Aussies will be hoping that this does not come back to haunt them.
Wide down the leg side, the batsman leaves it alone.
This time Burns is beaten as he misses the line of the delivery.
FOUR! This is full and wide outside off, Burns leans into the drive and caresses it through the cover region for a boundary.
Burns defends the last ball of the over off the back foot. End of an eventful over.
Spinning down the leg side, on the shorter side, Root moves back to pull but misses.

Shortish and outside off, Root waits and then tries to run it down. Cummins moves across to his left from backward point to stop the ball with a slide but misfields. The batsmen collect a couple of runs.
Stays back-footed to a short ball and punches it towards the on side.
Shortish again, outside off, Root moves across to cover the line and plays it down to point.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Once again Lyon is on the shorter side with his length and Joe punches it off the back foot to point.
Good bouncer by Cummins, on the middle and leg pole line, Burns ducks under it and the ball goes straight to Paine.
Burns shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid off by Burns.
Another length ball by Cummins, Burns blocks it out.
Short of a length ball just outside off, Burns sways away from it.
Bouncer on the last ball of the over, Burns ducks under this one. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Good ball to start the second session by Siddle, attacking the stumps straightaway. Root does well as he blocks it out straight back towards Peter.

Close one! Again Siddle goes for the stumps and gets his line right. Root this time looks to push this one down the ground but luckily gets an inside edge on that one. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take two.
Length ball around off, Root leaves it alone.
Fuller one this time, driven to the man at mid off.
Good length ball on off, Root has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

DROPPED! ROOT SURVIVES AGAIN! This is a juicy half volley outside off, inducing the drive from Root and he goes for it but he gets a thick outside edge on it. It goes wide to the right of Smith at second slip, he dives, gets two hands on it but he puts it down. The ball goes towards third man as the batters take one.
Length ball on middle and leg, Root looks to defend but is hit on the thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full ball just outside off, pushed towards the off side.

Jaffa from Hazlewood! This one is pitched on a good length, around off. It nips away after pitching, Root looks to drive it towards cover but misses it altogether. Looks to be his day. Even if he had nicked that, it might have either gone to an unmanned region or even if gone to hand, might have been put down.
Root blocks it out by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fullish on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone by Burns.
Outside off to Burns, he tries to block it but it goes off the edge wide of the slip cordon.
Full ball on middle and off, Burns defends it out.
On the hips of Burns, he looks to flick but misses and is hit on the thigh pad. It goes towards fine leg and the batters take two leg byes.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball outside off, Burns defends this one off the back foot.
Root gets up on his toes and blocks this one back towards the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Root.
Another one wide outside off, left alone by Root.
Length ball outside off, Root guides this towards point.

On the pads of Root, he looks to flick it towards the leg side but misses. The ball kisses his pads and rolls towards fine leg. The fielder in the deep is slow to get to the ball and that allows the batters to take two!

FOUR! 7000 Test runs for Joe Root! He becomes just the 12th Englishman and 4th fastest for them to achieve this feat and will be proud of it! Hazlewood dishes a full one outside off, Root leans into the shot and drives this through the cover-point region. The ball races to the fence.
Good length ball landing just outside off and nipping back in off the seam. Burns gets forward and across to work it on the leg side but misses and is hit high on the thigh pad.
This one is served on a length outside off, Burns has an easy leave.
Another watchful leave outside the off stump for Burns.

FOUR! Gorgeous extra cover drive to bring England's 100! Burns just leans into the fuller length ball and thumps it through the gap. The widish mid off fielder tries his best to stop it with a full length dive but fails in his effort. Great timing and placement, result is a cracking boundary. It's also a no ball for overstepping.
Too full in length on middle, Burns pushes it down to mid on for a run.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
A bit short and on middle, Root helps it off his pads but finds square leg.
Bouncer on the leg pole line, Burns ducks under it.
Full one just outside off, Burns pushes it towards mid on.
Play and a miss! Or is it? Short of a length ball just outside off, Burns initially looks to play at it but then takes his bat away at the last moment.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is out of nowhere. A wicket. Burns is out of here! Just 3 runs short of his half ton! This is short of a length ball on the off pole line, Burns looks to pull this one but gets a top edge on that one. It loops up in the air and goes towards short mid-wicket where Mitchell Marsh takes an easy catch. Burns is not as lucky as his skipper Root and he has to go back to the dugout. Australia will be relieved as they have finally broken the 76-run stand. The visitors with their tails up now.
Length ball outside off, Stokes chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

Shout for an lbw! Not entertained. A length ball on middle and leg, angling down, Root tries working it on the leg side but misses. He is hit on the pads, they appeal and Joe comes out of the crease in search of a run. He is sent back by his partner who was more engaged in watching the umpire and his decision.
Short in length and outside off, Root reaches out and chops his shot down past the gully fielder for a run.
Siddle switches to 'round the wicket and serves a back of a length ball outside off. Stokes keeps his bat close to his body as he looks to play inside the line. Gets beaten eventually.
Better leave this time by Ben. The line from Siddle is quite wide outside off, Stokes has nothing to do with it.
Edgy! This one straightens a bit after landing around off, Stokes is squared up in defense and edges it behind. It's done with soft hands and hence it doesn't carry to any fielder.
Interesting. Stokes gives the charge to the bowler. He walks forward and across before nudging a length ball off his pads to fine leg. He opens his account with a single.
On the shorter side by Hazlewood, Stokes gets on the back foot and pulls this towards backward square leg. The fielder in the deep mops it up as the batters take two.
Good length ball on middle and off, Stokes looks to block it out but gets an inside edge on it which goes onto hit the pads.
Ahead of a good length outside off, Stokes pushes this towards the off side.
Just outside off, on a good length, Stokes leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Stokes lets it through to Paine.
Outside off, left alone by Stokes again.
Fullish on the off pole line, Root pushes this towards mid off.
Another full ball, just outside off, Root pushes this one towards the man at point.
Good length ball on middle and off, Root blocks it straight towards Siddle.

Siddle pushes this full and around off, Root is induced into the drive but gets an inside edge on it. The ball goes past the leg pole and towards fine leg as the batters take one. Root, after getting three lives, should be looking to make the most of it and not throw away his wicket.
Stokes has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shortish ball on off, Stokes stands tall and pushes this one back towards mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Root pushes this one towards point.
Full and on middle and leg, Root flicks this one towards mid-wicket and takes one.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a couple. Stokes looking solid at the start of his innings.
Outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Another one outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length ball on the middle pole line, Stokes stands tall and pushes this one towards extra cover.
Good length ball just outside off, Root blocks it out.

A loud LBW appeal by the Aussies but turned down by the umpire. This is a good length ball on the off pole line, Root looks to push at it but fails to do so. The visitors thought that it hit the pad directly and hence appealed. The umpire turns it down and the replays show that he was correct, there was a big inside edge on that one. The batters take a single in the meantime as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
Short of a length ball on middle and off, Stokes pulls this one towards square leg and takes a couple.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Length ball on middle and off, Stokes blocks it out.
On the pads of Stokes, he works it towards backward square leg and takes a single. He was looking for the second but fell down after completing the first run.
FOUR! Fullish ball wide outside off, Stokes looks to drive it through covers with a flat bat but it goes through the mid off region off the toe end of the bat and towards the fence.
FOUR! Another boundary! This time Stokes was in full control as  he opens the face of his bat and guides this one wide of the slip cordon towards the third man fence.
Stokes looks to push it towards mid off but gets an edge on it which goes towards point. The fielder from gully dives to his left and saves at least a run for his side. The batter takes one.
Good length ball on middle and off, Root looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and on off, Root pushes this towards cover and takes a single.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes one to keep the strike.
Landed around off, watchfully defended.
Hint of inswing there and Stokes lets Root know about the same. Full and around off, coming in, watchfully blocked out.
Wow. Plenty of inswing on this occasion. Almost got through the gate. Full and around off, Ben looked to defend but the ball went off the inner half of the bat towards mid on. Marsh is smiling.
Good effort by Marsh but why? Might injure himself. A length ball, around middle, BS walks down the track and punches it down the ground. Marsh dives to his right and parries it towards mid off.
Walks down the pitch, does Stokes, to counter the swing and pushes it towards mid on.
Down the leg side, helped with the swing through square leg for a couple.
Down the leg side, Root looks to guide it fine down the leg side with one hand off his bat but misses it.
Length ball outside off, Root lets the ball go.
Outside off, Root plays it towards point.
Cummins bowls a length ball, Root looks to defend but gets an edge on that one.
A full ball after a long time by Cummins to Root, he drives it straight towards mid off.
Another full ball outside off, Root drives at it but it goes off the toe end of the bat towards cover where Wade gives it a chase and mops up. The batters take two in the meantime. DRINKS!
Full and around off, swinging in, solidly defended towards cover.
Landed around off, swinging in, Ben looks to defend but the ball goes off the inner half towards square leg.
A length ball around off, jagging back in, Ben looks to whip this away to the leg side but misses and is hit just around the box.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! Caught! Another wicket out of the blue. A short ball, outside off, Stokes looks to pull but seems like the ball never arrived. Was it a slower one or did Ben play a touch too early? Either way, a top edge was induced. The ball ballooned in the air and Nathan Lyon took it at point with fingers pointing skywards. He looked a touch nervous after that catch and Labuschagne consoles him. Replays now show that Stokes turned a full 360 degrees after playing that shot. He had no idea where the ball went, did not want to have an idea either, as he just stormed off. Assuming that the fielder would take the catch. If he were Root, he might have watched till the end, just in case even that went down. Australia would be happy with their progress post Lunch.
Outside off, left alone. Plenty of outswing in that one.
Outside off, fuller in length, driven straight to point.
Full and outside off, driven down the ground. Well stopped by the fielder.
Full and outside off, Root walks into the shot and drives it nicely through the covers. Three runs taken.
Down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a couple to get off the mark.
Full and outside off, driven crisply but straight to short extra cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses.
Short and outside off, punched to the off side.
Full and outside off, swinging away, Root watches it swing past.
A short ball, outside off, Joe fends it to the off side.
A length ball, on the pads, worked through square leg for a couple.
On a length outside off, solidly defended.

FOUR! ELEGANT! That has been the case with Siddle and Bairstow welcomes him in style. A gentle loosener, overpitching around off, Bairstow drives it straight back to where it came from, through mid on. The original Bairstow would have looked to flick it through mid-wicket. Jonny in the best of form would have hit this straight down the ground. Option B is just what we witnessed. Is a return to form on the cards then?

FOUR! Now on another part of the ground! This is not a bad ball but again, not much effort from Siddle. He lands it on a length but just lands it there. Not doing much with it. Bairstow just eases it through the covers for a boundary with a punch.
Outside off, left alone.

Now this is an effort ball. Full and fast, just outside off, Jonny looked to defend but the ball zipped back off the surface and nearly went through, hitting the pads of YJB. But there was an inside edge involved as well.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses. Paine dives to his left and takes it with one glove.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Landed outside off, Root gets on top of the bounce and punches it towards point. A single taken.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and outside off, swinging away, driven straight to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, this seems like a definite plan now. They are trying to get him caught down the leg side. Root misses his glance.

HALF CENTURY FOR ROOT! 4th in this series. He has been given three lives but it is not his problem if Australia want to celebrate Christmas so early. He has absorbed the pressure, taken everything in his stride and is now opening up slowly. Gets there with a late nudge towards fine leg, running hard for the second. To be honest, the danger period begins now for him. He has scores of 57, 71 and 77 this series and if any complaint comes against him, it is his poor conversion rate into a century. Not a bad time to ask for that present from the kangaroo-styled Santa Claus today.
Around off, defended solidly from the crease.
Landed outside off, let through to his counterpart.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Full and just around off, solidly kept out.
Full and outside off, swinging away, driven confidently towards short extra cover.
Landed outside off, tempting Jonny to drive but he is not tempted.
Full and outside off, more outswing, driven wide of cover but mid off mops it up.
A length ball, around middle, JB looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Landed outside off, let through once again.
FOUR! ELEGANT! He will not let this one go! Overpitched outside off, swinging away, Jonny drives it through the covers and this time he finds the gap.
Full and outside off, Root leans and drives it through the covers.
Landing outside off, Bairstow looks to flick but is early into the shot and gets a leading edge towards cover. Had to adjust late there.
Landed outside off, moving away, Jonny looks to defend but the away movement induces an outside edge. Not carrying to the slip cordon though.
Down the leg side, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
One more delivery down the leg side, Jonny looks to flick but misses this time.
4000 TEST RUNS FOR JONNY BAIRSTOW! Full and around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a couple. He becomes the 34th Englishman to reach this milestone.
Down the leg side, helped through fine leg for a single.
TWO BYES! Plenty of turn, but way down the leg side. Tim Paine is surprised as well and is not able to stop it, parrying it towards fine leg. Two runs taken.
Around middle and off, worked through the leg side for a single.

Interesting. A slightly short ball, around middle, Joe gets across and does what? A paddle. Yes, a paddle. When you know it is your day, you can do anything, can't you? This is slightly awkwardly hit through fine leg for a run.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Around off, worked through mid-wicket for one.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Landed outside off again, Root waits for the ball to come to him and guides it towards gully, who is late to stop it but backward point mops it up.
Outside off, on a length, Root looks to fish but then decides to bail out. Is late and is beaten.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full and around off, solidly defended.
A short ball, outside off, fended to the off side.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a single.
Full and just around off, watchfully blocked out.
The slider from Lyon, Root plays inside the line and is beaten.
Outside off, Joe lunges and pushes it towards cover for a quick single.
The slider again from the Goat, his fodder refuses to accept any grass. Lets it pass.
A short ball outside off, punched towards point.
Another short ball, again the skipper pushes it towards cover.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Full and just outside off, watchfully kept out.
Around middle, JR taps it in front of him and sets off but Hazlewood quickly gets across and has a kick at the striker's end. Root gets in by that time.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, Bairstow looks to flick but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat, past Marnus Labuschagne at short leg.
Down the leg side, helped through fine leg for a couple.
Another one down the leg side, tucked through fine leg for a run.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out.

Down the leg side, Joe looks to flick but misses. Paine collects and appeals but nothing from Erasmus. Lyon asks Smith about the review (yes, Smith and not Paine) but the former skipper shakes his head. Now Paine looks back for a confirmation and the shake of the head continues. Replays show that the ball hit the pad.
Full and around off, watchfully defended. TEA ON DAY 1!
First ball after Tea, it is a length ball on the off pole line, close to the body. Bairstow pushes it back towards Cummins.
Another length ball around off, Bairstow gets on his toes and pushes it towards extra cover.
Length ball outside off, Bairstow lets it through to Paine.
Full and outside off, Cummins trying to induce the drive. Bairstow obliges and drives it powerfully but straight to the fielder at mid off.
Short of a length outside off, Bairstow sways away from it.
Another one outside off, left alone by Jonny. A maiden to start off the last session of Day 1.
Good length ball on off, Root blocks it out.
Way outside off, Root leaves it alone. Paine dives low to his right and parries it towards the slip cordon.
Root has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side by Marsh, Root leaves it alone.
Good length ball just outside off, Root guides it to the man at point.
Fuller this time, Root pushes this one towards cover.
Good length ball on the off pole line, Bairstow pushes it back towards the bowler.

Again just outside off, Bairstow pushes this towards cover-point and sets off for a run. Root denies and Jonny has to rush back in as Wade is closing in on the ball. He grabs it and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Even if he had hit, Bairstow was well in. Good call by Root.
Bouncer this time on the off pole line by Cummins, Bairstow does well to duck under it.
Bairstow stands up on his toes and defends this one out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball around off, Bairstow again defends it out. Third maiden in a row and England are yet to score a run after the Tea break. Tight stuff by Australia.
Good length on off, Joe Root has played that one onto the off side.
Root looks to defend this one onto the off side but it goes off the inside edge and onto the pads.

First run in the third session of play and it has come after 20 balls. This is down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses. It goes straight through to Paine, to his left. He dives to his left and parries it. The batters take a bye as he gathers this one and throws it back towards Marsh.
Bairstow chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Another one outside off, left alone by Bairstow.
The batsman has punched that ball through the off side.

OUT! TIMBER! Root is finally gone and it looks like he is almost in disbelief. Another cracker from Cummins and guess who has he got? The opposition skipper again! Cummins gets Root for the third time this series and 7th overall - most against any batsman! A length ball, around off, Root looks to defend but this one pitches around middle and off and then nips away a bit. The ball stays low as well, goes past the outside edge and knocks the off stump back. This is exactly similar to the way Cummins got Root on the fourth evening of the Manchester Test. Root does not want to go. He is busy gardening the pitch! Now, he has a look at the replays and starts to walk back.
Landed outside off, Buttler shoulders arms. The ball comes back in a long way and shades of Old Trafford second innings come to mind. This one though, misses the off stump.
A length ball, wide outside off, left through.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Full and well outside off, let through.
Close shave! A length ball, outside off, Buttler looks to push this through the off side but gets a thick inside edge past the stumps towards fine leg! A single taken.

NOT OUT! Marsh bowls this one down the leg side, Buttler looks to flick but fails to do so. Paine gathers the ball and puts in a loud appeal along with his teammates. They think that he has nicked it and thus they go for the referral after umpire Erasmus turns it down. The replays roll in, Ultra Edge comes into play and shows that the ball has missed the bat. It has hit the thigh pad and that is what the noise was. Australia lose a review.
Buttler shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
FOUR! Superbly driven through the covers and he has a knack of at least playing one cover drive in his innings. This is full and outside off, Buttler leans into the drive and it races to the fence.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Length ball outside off, again left alone by Buttler.
Length ball on middle and off, Buttler blocks it out.

Jaffa from Cummins! He pitches this on a length, outside off, and gets it to shape away. Bairstow goes for a block but the ball goes past the outside edge. The Aussies put in a stifled appeal but nothing there. Paine juggles it once, twice and then the ball goes towards Warner who finally holds onto it.
Full and on off, the batsman has driven it through mid off.
Jonny chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Again Cummins beats the outside edge of Bairstow's bat as he looks to drive this one through the off side.
This time Bairstow tries to defend the length ball but it goes off the toe end towards the slip cordon all along the ground.
On the pads, Bairstow looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Buttler chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A quick single taken by Buttler as he tucks it towards short leg and sets off for the run. Bairstow responds and he is well in before the fielder could have his shy at the stumps.

OUT! LBW! That one is hitting middle and leg and one must say, a very good decision by umpire Marais Erasmus. Marsh bowls a beautiful reverse swinging yorker which hits Bairstow right on the left boot. Umpire Erasmus doesn't take much time in adjudging him out after the loud appeal from the Aussies. Bairstow is baffled at first but goes for the review with the final three seconds left. The replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracker now comes in, impact in line and going onto hit the middle and leg pole. England lose a review and they are in big trouble now.
Fullish ball outside off, Curran pushes it with soft hands towards cover and takes a single. First Ashes runs for him and England will be hoping that there are many more to come.
Full ball wide outside off, Buttler gets down and opens the face of his bat as he guides it towards third man for a couple.
Short of a length ball on middle and off, Curran initially looks to play at it but then sways away.
SIX! That is how you reply to a bumper! Another short ball on the off pole line, this time Curran doesn't sway away from it and hits it with power over fine leg for a maximum.
Curran looks to defend but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.

NO BALL! Drama in the Ashes will never come to an end! Curran had been adjudged LBW following an appeal by the Aussies. He had started to walk back as he knew it was plumb. Cummins pitched this on middle and got it to shape back in and Curran missed the ball to get hit in front of the stumps. Umpire Dharmasena gives it out LBW but he wants to check for overstepping. The replays roll in, and YES, Cummins has overstepped. Curran has been given a lifeline by the Aussies after Root was given three. Looks like it is Christmas Down Under.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Curran looks to block this one but misses to get hit on the pads.
Length ball on off,  defended off the back foot by the batsman.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another one outside off, left alone.

This time Marsh gets it closer to the wickets and makes Buttler play at it. He misses and is hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal from the Aussies and the umpire turns it down. It looks to be going down leg and the Australians are not interested in going for the review.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Full on middle and leg, Buttler pushes this powerfully towards mid on.
Bouncer to start off the over again to Sam Curran. He ducks under it.
Good length ball around off, Curran pushes this one through mid off and takes three as the fielders mop it up.
Full and on off, Buttler drives it straight to the fielder at mid on.
Buttler attempts to put bat on ball on this length ball but is beaten as he plays down the wrong line.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Buttler looks to push this one towards cover but it goes off the outer half through backward point for a boundary.
Full on middle and off, pushed towards the man at mid off.
FOUR! Counter-attack by Curran! This is short and wide outside off, Curran slashes at it and it goes through point for a boundary. Curran is not gonna hang back here.
The ball has taken the inside edge of the bat and goes down the leg side. They pick up a single.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full and on off, Buttler pushes it towards mid off.
Works this through square leg for a single.

OUT! Edged and taken. One shot too many by Curran. Does not make much use of the reprieve. He was let off on a no ball when on 7, but has been dismissed on 15. Full and outside off, Curran throws his bat at that, not looking to move his feet and this time nicks it behind. The ball flies thick and fast to Steven Smith at second slip who takes it near his head. He comes and departs (twice) in the span of 13 balls, does Curran.
Length ball on middle and off, Buttler defends it from within the crease.
Good length ball on middle and off, Buttler pushes this one towards extra cover but straight to the man.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Good length ball on middle and off, Buttler blocks this one out.
Outside off, left alone by Buttler.

FOUR! Power with precision! What a shot by Buttler! This one was full and outside off, Buttler crashes this one towards the cover and it goes to the fence like a trace of a  bullet. This also brings up the 200 for England.
On the pads of Woakes, he flicks it towards the man at square leg.
Full and wide outside off, Woakes drives this one beautifully through the covers. The fielder in the deep mops it up and the batters take two. Woakes is off the mark.
The ball is way wide on the leg side but the batsman still goes after it. Woakes misses and the ball is collected by Paine.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

OUT! LBW! Corker of a yorker by Marsh and Woakes is the one to walk back to the pavilion now. Marsh bowls a reverse swinging yorker on the leg pole line, Woakes looks to dig this one out but misses the ball completely. As soon as it hits the boot of Woakes, the Australian players appeal and umpire Erasmus raises his finger. Woakes has a short talk with his partner Buttler but he advises him against taking the review. Woakes starts taking the long walk back. The Ball Tracker confirms that the umpire was right as the ball is hitting the bottom of middle and leg. The change of bringing in Mitchell Marsh for Travis Head in the playing XI has worked wonders for the visitors as he has picked up a 4-fer already.
Archer has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Slapped on the face! Poor technique from Buttler. A short ball, well-directed, Jos is late in picking the length, tries to move away but fails to do so. He takes a blow on his chest and then it deflects onto the grille of the helmet. No harm done to Buttler.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, Buttler allows it through.

Sliced away! Fullish and outside off, Buttler tries playing the cover drive but it takes the outer half and races through point. Lyon moves swiftly across to his left from sweeper cover, dives like a lion and then saves a certain boundary. Two runs added to the total.
Misses everything! Short in length and outside off, Buttler tries pulling it across the line but misses.
Hazlewood lands this one on a length and outside off, Buttler plays a mistimed drive towards covers.
At 87.4 mph, Josh delivers a full ball on off, angling in, Buttler blocks it back and it rolls past the bowler to mid on.
Good length delivery close to off, Archer plays near his body and taps it down to point.
Another length ball, around off, Archer stays back and pushes it with an angled bat to point again.
Attempted inswinger from Mitch. On a good length outside off, Archer chases and gets a bottom edge onto it. Nearly a drag on there, nearly a fifer...
Sliding down the leg side, Jofra tries to flick but fails to middle his shot. It goes off his pads to square leg.
Jofra misses out there! A full length ball drifting down the leg side, Archer tries his best to flick but misses.

Marsh goes full throttle. Attempts to hurl in an inswinging yorker but it turns out to be a low full toss on off, Archer pushes it in the gap at covers for a single. Buttler not looking to farm strike as of now.
FOUR! Archer takes on the challenge and finds the fence. Short delivery, around off, it doesn't get high enough to bother the batsman and Jofra pulls it with authority to the deep mid-wicket fence.

With a short mid-wicket in place and the deep square leg fielder standing a few steps ahead, Paine sends the signal for some short pitch bowling. But it turns out to be a double bluff from Josh. He bowls an inswinger on a length outside off, Archer is beaten on the inside edge as he attempts to block from the crease.
Good length ball close to off, Archer succeeds this time in blocking from the back foot.
A rib tickler on this occasion. Rising around leg, Archer stands tall and taps it down wide of Wade at short leg.

FOUR! Gloved away! Hazlewood digs in a short ball down the leg side, Archer gloves his attempted pull shot behind. Paine flies to his left but it's quite wide of him and races away to the fine leg fence.
A couple of shorter ones followed by a fullish delivery on off. Archer, himself being a bowler, expects this and defends it safely to the off side.
Back of a length ball on off, Buttler remains back and mistimes his punch down to mid on.
Away swinger from Peter. In the zone outside off, an easy leave for Buttler.
Closer to the off stump this time. A length ball, angling in, Buttler closes the face of the bat and pushes it softly to mid-wicket.
Shortish and on off, Buttler punches it to the right of Wade at short cover. He dives and gets fingertips on it. Parries it to the right of mid off and the batsmen take a run.
Good length ball outside off, a hint of reverse swing, Archer calmly covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Another reverse swinging delivery, nipping in from a length around off, Archer does well to play late and defend it to the leg side.

EDGY FOUR! Slightly short in length and around off, Buttler hangs on the back foot in an attempt to work it across the line but it takes the outer half of his bat and races away from the slip cordon for a boundary.

FOUR! Streaky again! This time it drops in front of first slip. A length ball on off, Buttler tries playing straight but it straightens to gather the outside edge. It falls in front of Warner and speeds past him to the fence. Lucky escapes for Jos!
Taps it down with soft hands towards point for a run.

OUT! Regulation catch for Tim Paine! Wicket number 8 goes down for England. Hazlewood hurls in a length ball close to off, Archer tries to play the line but the ball straightens a bit to catch the outside edge. Tim Paine makes no mistake and there are no heroics from Archer with the bat. The lower order not stepping up here for England will worry them. Usually, they bail out after the failure of the top batsmen. Can they reach 250 from here?
Short and down the leg side, Leach sways away from the line of fire.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Leach shuffles across a bit and defends it down to short leg.
Good length ball on off, Buttler walks forward and blocks it down watchfully.
Short in length and on off, Buttler drags his pull off the inside half to deep square leg. He takes a single.
Back of a length ball on off, angling in, Leach defends it off his back foot.
Switches to 'round the wicket for Leach. Serves a full length ball outside off and it jags back in sharply. Leach does well to keep it out.
Returns to bowling over the wicket. Delivers a shortish ball on middle and off, Leach inside edges his attempted back foot defense onto the thigh pad.
Drifting down the leg side, Leach clips it behind square leg and returns for the second run. Opens his account on the sixth ball he faced.
SIX! Jos Buttler in the Twenty20 avatar! Back of a length delivery outside off, Jos spots the room, hangs on the back foot and towers it over long off for a biggie.

SIX! Boom! Hazlewood is under the pump! He delivers it in the hitting zone of the batsman. Buttler aligns himself and launches it over long on this time. Bye bye ball. This is exhilarating stuff from Jos. The crowd is brought back to life.

Misses this time! Buttler tries to be cheeky on this occasion. Attempts for a paddle shot to a length ball outside off. Fails to connect properly and it hits him on the pads. Words and smiles exchanged, so good to watch. The crowd is into it as well.
Spears in a very full ball on middle, Buttler tries heaving it over the mid-wicket region probably but it takes the inner half and runs behind square leg for a run.
On middle and leg, Leach helps it behind square leg and wants two. But Labuschagne is quick to the ball and they have to be satisfied with a run.

Buttler plays a dot. Leach will be on strike. This still counts? This plan? We have seen Leach dealing with the Aussie bowlers with ease over the course of this Test series. On middle and off, a touch short, Buttler punches from the back foot but finds the mid-wicket fielder. 14 from the over, an eventful one for England.
Very full and around off, Leach tries to dig it out but misses. Marsh is feeling his hamstring. Does some stretching with the help of Pat Cummins before returning to his mark.
Beaten again! A good length ball landing on off and angling away from the batsman, Leach plays inside the line and is beaten.
Short in length and on middle, Leach is solidly behind the line in defense. He just goes on his toes and calmly blocks it to the off side.
Too full in length and around leg, Leach gets across his stumps and flicks it fine down the leg side for one. Had he missed, he would have been a plumb lbw candidate.
Short in length and outside off, Buttler swings and misses.
Yet another swing and a miss for Buttler. He attempts for a pull shot to a short delivery but misses. Yells in disgust. Again, Leach is on strike for the next over. Can Australia work him over?
Slanting away from the batsman outside off, Leach pushes at it and misses.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fuller and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short around leg, jumping onto the batsman, Leach fends it away over short leg.
Again a shortish delivery around leg, Leach works it wide of Wade towards deep square leg. Wants a run but Buttler denies.

Interesting. Declined the single on the last ball and have taken it this time. Full and outside off, a glorious drive from Leach and it's to the right of mid off. The fielder there slides and makes the stop. Seems Buttler thought there were two runs on offer. Miscalculation.
Digs in a short ball on leg, Leach ducks away from the firing line.
Lands it on a length close to off, Leach defends it off his front foot.
Straighter delivery, Leach flicks it past the right side of Wade at short leg and crosses for a run. The mid-wicket fielder does the mop up job.
Full and sliding down the leg side, Buttler tries his best to power it over the on side but misses.
Fullish and on the pads, it's clipped to deep mid-wicket for a run. Leach cleans his specs and gets ready to face the last ball. Getting his job again.

EDGED, FOUR! Cummins runs in from 'round the wicket and delivers a full ball close to off. It straightens a touch after landing and Leach tries to play the line. It takes the outside edge and flies past the right side of the diving gully fielder. A boundary to bring up England's 250!

Short in length and on middle, Buttler swivels and pulls it through square leg. Labuschagne at deep backward square leg is late to pick it up but then does well to stop the ball. The batsmen take two. The sun is staring straight down to Marnus and he has his goggles resting on the back of his cap. Hmm... adding to his style quotient!

SIX! This one has gone all the way, to the right of Marnus Labuschagne this time! Another short ball by Josh to Jos and it has been dispatched via a thunderous pull shot behind square leg. High and handsome it goes into the crowd, bringing out a humongous roar from them. Fifty up for Buttler, his 15th in Tests, first in the Ashes. He's taking the fight to Australia and trying to maximize the English total to as far as possible.
Spears in a very full ball on middle, Buttler brings his bat down in time to dig it out towards mid on.
Slips a full ball down the leg side, Buttler fails to put any bat behind this one.
Short in length and way down the leg side, Buttler chases it in an attempt to pull and gets a bottom edge. It rolls to fine leg and Leach will have one ball to deal in this over.
Survives. Leach shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot. 9 from the over, 24 in Hazlewood's last three.
A leg spinner on the shorter side outside off, Buttler mistimes his square cut to point.

FOUR! Good shot, great shot! Sometimes you curse T20 cricket for what it has done to Test cricket but this is the one dimension in batting it has added in the longer version. Flighted full ball on middle, Buttler brings out the reverse sweep and nails it behind point for a boundary.

DROPPED! Very full and on middle, Buttler drills it back to the bowler who sticks his right hand out but fails to hold on. It deflects behind but they decide not to cross. A tough chance and these catches sometimes stick, sometimes don't.
Quicker and on the pads, worked on the leg side through mid-wicket but no run taken.
Shortish and outside off, punched to sweeper cover for one.
Too full in length around leg, Leach plays it out past Wade and looks for a run. Not taken.
Serves a length ball in the region outside off, Buttler swings but fails to connect.
Good length around off, Jos shuffles across and blocks it well.
Straighter line, Buttler works it with soft hands in the gap at mid-wicket, good enough for a couple.
Fullish and on leg, Buttler plays a well-timed on drive but declines the run.
Fullish and on middle and leg, Buttler flicks but finds Warner at mid-wicket.

Fuller in length and on middle, Buttler helps it through the gap at mid-wicket and runs a single. Warner ambles behind the ball, giving the opportunity to Jos to take another run but Buttler ain't doing that, of course.
Short in length and outside off, Buttler pulls it to deep mid-wicket. No run taken.
On the pads, worked on the leg side, straight to mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fullish and going down the leg side, Buttler clips it to deep mid-wicket and decides to give Leach two balls to survive the over.
Good length ball on middle and off, Leach is on his toes as he blocks it back.
Well bowled and equally well played. An inswinging yorker around off, Leach brings his bat down in time to block it out.
Back of a length ball on off, Buttler defends it from the back foot to the off side. The hard nut will come onto the bat nicely also.

Shot! Full and drifting down the leg side, Buttler picks it up off his pads and flicks it over mid-wicket. There is no fielder in the deep but the ball doesn't have enough legs to cross the fence. Two runs taken.
Beaten comprehensively! Cummins pitches it up and outside off, Buttler tries to play an expansive cover drive but is beaten by the away movement.
Uppish but safe! Good length ball angling in on middle, it probably sticks on the surface a bit as Buttler is early into his shot. He checks his on drive and it goes wide of mid on.
Play and a miss! Back of a length ball on off, shaping in, Buttler clears his front leg for a big heave-ho over the leg side but misses. It travels over the stumps.
Beaten again! Fuller and wide outside off, nipping away, Jos tries to play the drive without much footwork and gets beaten.
Solid! Full in length and outside off, Leach is confidently on the front foot as he defends.

Appeal for a catch, not given and Tim Paine returns. Was there any glove? No, is the answer. Short ball on middle, Leach tries to move away from the line of fire but fails to do so cleanly. It balloons behind off something and the gully fielder takes a diving catch. They appeal, nothing from the umpire. Paine consults Wade who was standing at short leg that whether Leach's arm-guard was in contact with the wrist band. That's very hard to tell. Even the replays are inconclusive.
Bouncer! The batsman does well to evade it.
On middle and leg, Leach defends it off his back foot to the leg side.
Short in length and around off, Jack defends it off his back foot again.

A very harmless delivery to end the day's play. Full and way down the leg side, Leach tries flicking but misses. A good take by the Aussie skipper with a dive. That will be it for the day. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Cummins starts with a fuller ball on middle, Buttler punches it firmly but straight to mid on.
Good length ball outside off this time, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and on off and middle, blocked towards cover by Buttler.

Good length ball outside off, Buttler walks across the off stump to work it down the leg side but gets hit on the pads. He was hit outside the line and hence no appeal. The ball goes towards square leg as they cross for a leg bye. First runs of the day.
Fuller ball, pushed towards cover this time by Leach to pinch a single off the first ball he faced.

FOUR! Crunched through covers. Cummins ends the over with a poor ball outside off on a fuller length. Buttler stands in the crease and hammers this one through the cover region. The boundary brings up the 50-run stand between the two. Very vital runs these.
He starts with a fuller length ball outside off, Leach lets it go to the keeper.
Play and a miss. This time Leach goes for the drive to this full ball outside off, but can't get bat on ball.
FOUR! Slammed this time to perfection. Another fuller ball outside off, Leach gets into the position and times this through cover-point to get his first boundary of the day.
Another fuller ball on the fourth stump line, Leach pushes this off the front foot through extra covers to get a couple. Leach wanted another run but is denied by Buttler.
Fuller one on middle, defended solidly by Leach.
Wide outside off this time, Leach is not bothered as he shoulders arms.
Full on the pads, Buttler strokes it straight to mid on.
Fuller on off this time, Buttler blocks this towards mid on.
Another fuller ball on off, another firm push but straight to the mid on fielder.

FIVE WIDES! Bangs in short but it is way down the leg side. Paine's diving attempt to his left is in vain too. Buttler had gone across the leg stump to pull but it went further down the leg side and to the fine leg fence.
Fuller ball on middle this time, Buttler uses his wrists and flicks it for a single towards deep mid-wicket.
Beaten! Good ball this one. Shortish ball on middle, shapes away from the left-hander. Leach hangs his bat to push but the ball beats the outside edge.
Another shortish ball that goes past the outside edge of Leach. This is banged on middle again and shapes away from the bat of Leach. Lucky escape.
Full ball to start from Marsh. This is around off, Buttler pushes this firmly towards mid on.

Good length ball around off, Buttler works it towards mid on as the ball goes through the diving silly mid on fielder. David Warner is stationed there for these firm aerial punches coming from Buttler.
Wide outside off, Buttler crunches this through point but for no run.
On the pads this time on a fullish length, Buttler works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Fuller ball around off, Leach gets right behind the line to block.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky runs these. Good length ball on middle from Marsh. Leach looks to block it but the hint of away movement means the ball takes the thick outside edge and flies through gully for a boundary.

OUT! TIMBER! Cummins strikes and Buttler is out of here but not before playing a very handy innings of 70 runs. Buttler wants to heave this fuller ball outside off over the long on fence but the ball takes an inside edge onto the pads and then goes to hit the off stump. He has taken England's score closer to 300 runs. End of a valuable 68-run stand too. How many can the new batter Stuart Broad add along with Jack Leach?
Shortish ball around middle, Broad stands tall to block.
Good length ball outside off, Broad lets it go to the keeper.
Outside edge but falls short of the second slip fielder. Another back of a length ball on middle, Broad plays this with soft hands and hence that didn't carry.
Another bumper. Cummins continues to bang it short. Broad does well to sway away.
And another bouncer. Broad sways away to see off the over.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Fifer on return for Mitchell Marsh, his first in Tests. This is a good length ball on middle, Leach looks to block but is a little too slow in getting his bat down. He tries to block it onto the ground but the ball takes the bottom edge and bounces back on the stumps. Marsh bowled well yesterday and the fifer is a testimony of his brilliant effort. A top replacement this one. ENGLAND ALL OUT FOR 294.
Broad starts with a good length ball outside off, Warner lets it go to the keeper. He has been Broad's bunny all Ashes. He would not want to fall for him again.
Chases this time! Poor from Warner. He has been in that kind of form that he wants runs. This is a wide delivery outside off, wider than the last ball. Warner decides to go for it but misses.

No duck this time! Broad dishes this on a fuller length on middle, Warner pushes this towards cover and takes off for a run. Australia are underway too. David will be a relieved man, he bagged a pair in the last Test.
Good length ball around off, Harris blocks it towards point.
Fuller ball on middle this time, Harris pushes this towards mid off.
Too wide to make the batter play this time. Harris lets it go the keeper.
Archer starts with a good length ball, closer to off stump, Warner taps it towards point.

EDGY FOUR! Archer goes fullish this time. Warner looks to drive but the ball takes a thick outside edge and it goes to the  right of the diving gully fielder and through to the third man fence. First boundary for Warner and Australia.
On the pads this time, Warner looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the pads.
Fuller ball this time. Warner strokes it straight to point.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Warner has to walk back. Oh boy, is he disappointed? Is he angry? The look on his face seems like an obedient student who has just been asked to go home as a punishment from his school principal. Poor bloke. Cannot buy a run. Back of a length ball wide outside off, Warner is run-hungry as he throws his bat at it again but misses. There is no feet movement at all but a noise is generated as the ball goes past the bat. The slip cordon instantly appeals but there is nothing much from Bairstow. He appeals after seeing the others appealing. Root goes for the review after thinking for a while. The naked eye does not show much, as there seems to be a gap between bat and ball. The Ultra Edge is taking ages to arrive. Finally, it does and there's a tickle as the ball gets closer to the bat. Almost at the toe end. Warner has to walk back. For a change, not to Broad. He walks off with loud boos from the crowd. His poor run in the series continues. Exactly the kind of start the hosts would've wanted.
On the pads on middle, Marnus looks to work it fine down the leg side but can't get bat on ball. He is hit high on the pads.
Harris is off the mark! Fuller ball on the pads, Harris tucks it nicely through mid-wicket to get three.
Appeal for an LBW but no review from England this time. Gets the ball to come back in with the angle. Marnus looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the pads.
On middle, a fuller ball, Marnus works it down the leg side and wants two straightaway. There is an appeal for a run out at the striker's end but he is well in. He is off the mark with that.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Misses his line this time as this one goes down the leg side. Marnus wants to pull but misses. Bairstow does well to stop it by going to his left.
FOUR! Gets the pull right this time. Banged short on middle by Broad, Labuschagne swivels and hammers the pull through the mid-wicket fence. Top shot that from Marnus.
Fuller ball, pushed towards mid off.
Beaten! Superb ball this time. Good length and closer to the body and shaping away. Harris looks to block but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
In the channel on a good length. Harris lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller ball around off, Harris wants to drive but the ball takes the inner half of the willow and goes back to the bowler.
On the pads on a fullish length. Harris looks to work it down the leg side but can't get bat on ball. He takes one on the pads.
Length ball wide outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another length ball outside off, Labuschagne lets it through to Bairstow.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one too.
In the channel this time, Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller one middle and off this time, blocked off the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus is late in taking the bat away as the ball takes the toe end of the bat and goes to the keeper on the bounce. Lucky!
Good length ball angled into the batter, Harris looks to block but is hit on the pads. Too high to make an appeal for the LBW.
Outside off this time, left alone.
Good length ball on middle again, this one shapes a hint away. Harris looks to block but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the fielder at gully on the bounce.
Slightly fuller this time from Archer. Harris looks to block but another outside edge goes towards Buttler at gully who does well to stop.

OUT! Caught! Archer strikes again! Australia in trouble early on as both the openers are back in the hut for them, yet again. Two outside edges fell short of the gully fielder but the third one goes straight to second slip. Stokes is superb in holding on to this one, very close to the ground. It is a good length ball closer to the off pole, Harris is squared up as he looks to block but the ball straightens a bit from there to take the outside edge. It flies to Stokes at second slip who takes it very low by going down. Australia have again started the innings very badly and need a big partnership now. David Warner is taking away all the criticism for his poor form and that has somehow protected Marcus Harris who has been equally poor in this series. Unlike Warner though, his time is running out with a few vying his spot in the Playing XI.
Bouncer to welcome Smudge! Smith ducks under it.
Outside off, Marnus lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish length ball this time, Marnus goes after it but misses.

On the pads this time. Labuschagne works it towards the leg side but Buttler at short leg is too sharp to let this one go through. Gets the ball and has a shy at the stumps but misses. Marnus never went out though.
This one is fuller, Labuschagne pushes this towards mid on.
Fuller one on off this time, pushed back to Broad.
Another fuller ball, Marnus strokes it straight to the mid on fielder.
Smith is beaten! Fuller ball around off, Smith goes for the drive but misses.

Another fuller ball on middle, Smith pushes this back to the bowler who collects the ball and throws it back at the striker's end. That wasn't needed though as Smith never ventured out of the crease. Probably, Archer trying to send the message that Smith is a marked man.
Shortens his length this time but it goes down the leg side. Smith lets it go.
Fuller around off this time, blocked nicely this time.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards point.
Good length ball around off, Smith walks across the off pole and blocks well.
FOUR! Whipped off the pads from Marnus. Broad dishes a fuller ball on the pads of Labuschagne. He is not going to miss out on that one as it is flicked nicely through mid-wicket for another boundary.
A single to follow the boundary. Fuller one around off this time, Labuschagne pushes it towards point to get off strike.
Good length ball around off, Smith blocks it back to the bowler.
Another good length ball but this is too wide to make Smith play.
Nicely done to get off the mark. Broad is targeting the stumps of Smith here. Smith reads that well and clips this fuller ball towards square leg to get a couple.
Good length ball around the fourth stump line, Smith works it through square leg for a run this time to get a single. 8 runs from the over.
Fuller ball around off, Smith strokes it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball this time, Smith walks across again to work it down the leg side but is hit on the pads.
Bouncer from Archer. Smith ducks under it.
Smith is beaten again! Archer bangs one short and makes it shape away from Smith. He looks to crunch a cut but misses. A great battle between the two at the moment.
Wide outside off this time, Smith lets it go to the keeper.
In the channel outside off this time, Smith leaves it alone.
Starts with a fuller ball around off, Labuschagne drives it towards point who does well to relay the ball towards the cover fielder on the dive. No runs taken.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Labuschagne blocks this towards mid on.
FOUR! CREAMED! Curran dishes a fuller ball outside off to Labuschagne. He leans into the drive and creams it through covers. He is looking in good touch here.

Appeal for a caught behind! Fuller ball outside off, Labuschagne goes for the drive but can't connect. Bairstow behind the wicket catches and appeals. Nothing from the umpire. Replays show that the sound was because of the bat hitting the ground. Good decision.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Another ball outside off, Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Smith goes for the cut but finds the gully fielder on the bounce.

Good shot from Smith. Slightly fuller around off, Smith drives this through covers nicely. The ball doesn't have the legs to reach the fence. Leach from cover hares after the ball and pulls it back in play. Interestingly, Leach, a left-hander, throws the ball with his right hand. Seems he is one of those ambidextrous cricketers. The Aussies need to be aware about that. Three runs added to the total.
Good length around off, blocked off the back foot.
In the channel this time, Labuschagne covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Another leave as this is outside off on a good length.
Fuller ball outside off, Smith does his antics with the bat after leaving the ball.

Play and a miss! Smith looking slightly fishy here. Another fuller ball angling away from him. He wants to drive it but fails to put bat on ball. Curran here brings a different challenge for Smudge. His left-arm angle adds a different dimension to the English attack and the Australian talisman needs to be watchful about that, especially early on in his innings. Shuffling across the stumps too much might cost him as Curran has the ability to swing it back into the batsman as well.
Fuller ball on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket by Smith to get a couple.
Curran is targeting the stumps as he delivers this fuller ball on middle, Smith does well to block off the front foot.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Fuller ball outside off, Smith is not going to miss out on this one. He leans into the drive and thumps it through cover-point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball around off, tapped towards mid off by Labuschagne.
Good length ball again but too wide to make Labuschagne play. He lets it go to the keeper.
Another ball outside off, Marnus makes another leave.
Slightly shorter one but again outside off, Labuschagne is not bothered as he shoulders arms.
Short one on the body, Labuschagne goes back and blocks.

Beaten! Bangs it in short, slightly. Labuschagne looks to work it away but the ball is angled into him. The ball sneaks past the inside half of his bat and heads over to the stumps. Lucky not to get an inside edge. Bairstow does well to pouch that one to his left.
Fuller ball around off, pushed back to the bowler by Smith.
Quick single this time. Smith pushes this towards mid off and calls for a run instantly.
Down the leg side this time. Labuschagne looks to guide it with a glance but misses.

EDGY FOUR! Goes fuller this time and makes Labuschagne go for the drive. He goes for it but the ball takes the outside edge and flies between second slip and third slip and to the third man fence. There is a gap between the two slips and it went through that. Stokes made a diving attempt to his right at second slip but the ball eluded him.
In the channel this time, Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller ball around off, driven firmly but straight to mid off.
On the pads of Smith by Woakes, he flicks it towards deep square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! On the pads from Woakes. Labuschagne lunges forward and flicks this nicely through mid-wicket for a boundary.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Another poor ball on the pads. Labuschagne stays in his crease and glances it towards the fine leg fence for another boundary. Replays showed that Bairstow made a diving attempt to his left but it was too far from his reach.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Back of a length ball around middle, blocked off the back foot by Labuschagne.
