Huge appeal for an lbw but not given! Root is having a word with the bowler and suggesting that this might have been high. Decides against the review. Smith shuffles to work it down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. England don't review and rightly so as the Ball Tracker rolls in to show that this was going over the off pole.

And again. Another appeal but nothing from the umpire once more. Smith is not sure which one is coming and which one is going away from him. A clueless Smith is a rarity. This is pitched around off. Smith shuffles across the off pole again but eventually doesn't play at it thinking that it will carry on with the angle of the bowler. But it straightens a bit to hit him flush on the pads. Skipper Root again has a word with the bowler and his mates but decides against the review. The Ball Tracker arrives and it shows that it was missing the off pole comfortably as it didn't come back enough into the batsman. Curran troubling Smith here. Good contest.
Bouncer now! Smith sways away from it.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fuller ball this time, pushed towards mid-wicket.

And again. Smith shuffles across and wants to leave this one but the ball comes back in just a hint to hit him on the pads again. Impact is outside off. Testing over this one from Curran to the man in form.
Good length delivery just outside off, Labuschagne blocks this one out.
Touch fuller this time, Labuschagne blocks it towards cover-point.
FOUR! On middle and leg this one by Woakes, Labuschagne shuffles across and flicks this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary. This also bring up 50 runs for Australia.
Marnus shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot back towards the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Labuschagne.

Good bowling by Woakes. He pitches this one on a length and gets it to straighten. Labuschagne looks to block this one but the ball hits the splice of the bat and goes towards the slip cordon on the bounce.

Length ball just outside the leg pole line, Smith shuffles and tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal by the England players but nothing serious. The ball rolls towards fine leg as the batters take a leg bye.
Yorker to Labuschagne by Curran, he digs this one out at the last moment.
Outside off, left alone by Labuschagne.
On the pads of Marnus, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Smith.
Down the leg side this one, Smith looks to flick but misses and the ball carries to Bairstow. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Starts by bowling a good length ball just outside the off pole line. Labuschagne knows exactly where his wickets are and shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Beautiful flick by Labuschagne! This one is full and on the off pole line, Marnus shuffles across and flicks this one through mid-wicket for a boundary. Lots of oohs and aahs by the English fielders! First boundary of the session this.
Good length ball on middle and off, Labuschagne blocks it out.
Outside off, length ball. Left alone by Labuschagne.
Good yorker by Archer on the leg pole. Labuschagne is quick to pick it up and flicks it towards fine leg for one.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Smith.
Wide outside off stump, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on middle and off, Labuschagne blocks it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Uppish and over the gully fielder. Labuschagne played this shot a bit like Joe Denly. Full and wide outside off, Labuschagne looks to drive at this one but it goes off the outside edge uppishly towards backward point to the fence. The 50-run stand is up between the solid duo now!
Broad pulls the length back on this one, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fullish on off, pushed towards the man at cover.
Bouncer down the leg side, Smith ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Steven Smith
Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith pushes this one towards mid on.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Fullish outside off, Labuschagne tries to block it out but it goes off the outside half of his bat towards point.
Labuschagne chooses to leave this length ball outside his off pole.
FOUR! What a shot by Smith! A treat to the eyes! This is a short of a length ball outside off, Smith gets up on his toes and punches this square through point for a boundary.
Fuller this time, Smith punches this towards the man at cover who collects it on the bounce.
Another fuller one outside off, Smith again pushes this towards cover.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Steven Smith lets the ball go through to Bairstow.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.

Good ball to start off by Archer, he bowls this one on a good length just outside the off pole. It nips back in just a bit and hits the pads of Labuschagne but off the inside edge. The England players did go up for an appeal but soon realised there was an inside edge on it.
Bouncer on the leg pole line, Labuschagne looks to duck under it and falls while doing it. He is down on the ground and having a laugh.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the pads of Labuschagne, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Another one on the pads, Smith flicks this one towards backward square leg and takes a couple.
Full and outside off, Smith pushes this with soft hands towards cover and takes a single to retain strike.
Length ball outside off, Smith makes a comfortable leave.
Another one outside off, left alone by Smudge.
Broad goes fuller this time, Smith pushes it powerfully towards the man at mid on.
Broad gets some inswing on this one. He pitches this one outside off, Smith makes the leave and then realizes that it is coming back in. It goes past the stumps but way too close for comfort.
Short and wide, Smith tries to cut it powerfully but fails to do so as he hits it straight to Roy (sub) at cover-point.
FOUR! This time Smith does not miss out as he crunches this full delivery wide outside off through the cover region for a boundary. Lovely flowing shot!
Labuschagne shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle and off, Marnus pushes it back towards Archer.
Another one, similar line and length, Labuschagne looks to tuck it towards the leg side but it goes off the outer half of his bat back towards Archer.
Outside off, left alone by Marnus.

OUCH! That has hit Labuschagne on the back of his elbow and he has straightaway signaled the physio to come out. This one is just behind a good length on the off pole line, there is some extra bounce on this as Labuschagne misses his defense. The ball goes past his bat but hits him on the back of the elbow and he is down on the ground in pain. He signals for the physio towards the dressing room.
Length ball just outside off, Labuschagne pushes this one off the back foot towards extra cover.
Woakes starts off with a good length ball on middle and off, Smith blocks it back towards Woakes.
Similar delivery to the previous one, Smith this time pushes it towards mid off.
Down the leg side this time, Smith tries to flick but misses. The ball goes past him and through to Bairstow.
Steven shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Another one down the leg side, again Smith goes for the flick but misses. Bairstow gathers it comfortably.
Outside off, left alone by Smith. A maiden to start off the new spell for Woakes.
Good length ball just outside off, Labuschagne blocks it out.
Short of a length on the body of Labuschagne, he plays it with soft hands onto the ground towards the leg side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Archer bowls this one just outside off on a length and gets it to shape away from Labuschagne. He goes for the back foot defense but it goes off the outer half past the gully fielder and into the third man fence. Loose bottom hands assisted him there.
Length ball  on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good bouncer by Archer! On the leg pole line, it shoots off the surface and Labuschagne does well to get out of the way.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
On the pads of Smith, he tucks it towards square leg.
Smith shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Another one on the pads, Smith flicks this one towards mid-wicket.
Fullish on off, Smith blocks it out towards mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Bouncer to end the over by Woakes, Smith does well to evade it.
Good length ball, nipping back in, Labuschagne looks to flick this one towards the leg side but only manages to get an inside edge onto the pad. It rolls towards fine leg as the batters take two.

OUT! LBW! Finally the partnership is broken and some respite for the hosts! Archer is the man again as he has taken all the wickets until now. This one is a similar delivery to the previous one, good length ball just outside off and nipping back in. This time Labuschagne misses his flick altogether and is hit flush on the pads. The English players all go up together for the appeal and umpire Erasmus agrees. Labuschagne walks up to his partner Steven Smith, has a long extended chat with him but eventually decides against taking the review as the time also runs out. Ball Tracker confirms that the umpire's decision is right as it shows three reds. The threatening 69-run stand is broken and this might be the window that the hosts were craving for.
First ball for Wade, he shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the front foot.

Comical! Everyone is having a laugh. This one is full and outside off, Wade pushes this one through mid off and sets off. They decide to run the third one on the throw and Smith speeds to the striker's end. Bairstow there acts to collect the throw while the ball is gathered in between by Archer near the non-striker's end. Seeing Jonny getting into the act, Smudge puts in a big dive to get inside the crease. Everyone is laughing. Isn't faking in the field against the rules? Debatable.
FOUR! Full and on the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good length ball outside off to start the fresh over by Woakes. Wade lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller this time, Wade drives it straight but Archer from mid off stops it.
Good length ball outside off again, it is shaping away from Wade. He lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Driven handsomely. Woakes overpitches this outside off, Wade leans into the drive and pierces the gap between cover and point. First boundary for him. Australia behind by 200 now.
Outside off again, left alone by Wade.
Good length ball on middle this time, Wade taps it towards mid off.
Almost! What a start by Curran! Corker of a yorker and Smith does well to dig it out at the last moment.
Outside off by Curran, left alone by Smith.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Similar ball, same result. Again on the pads, Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes another couple.

Another couple! Smith just does not miss out on any balls on his middle and leg pole. He shuffles across and plays it square this time towards deep square leg and takes two. Good batting by Smudge. With this, Australia have touched the 100-run mark.
Good length and outside off, Smith pushes this towards mid off.
Length ball wide outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Similar delivery, left alone by Wade again.

NOT OUT! Missing the off pole! Curran bowls this one on a length and on the off pole line, he gets it to nip back in a bit. Wade looks to block it out but misses the ball to get hit on the back pad. The England players go up in a big appeal but the umpire does not agree with them. After having a chat with his mates, Joe Root goes for the review. Ultra Edge comes into play, there is a spike as the ball passes the bat but the third umpire wants to have a look at the Ball Tracker also. On the third umpire's wish, the Ball Tracker comes into play. It shows that the ball is missing the off pole. England lose their review but one must think that why did the umpire go to the Ball Tracker if there was a spike as the ball went past the bat. Hmm... Imagine the controversy had the Ball Tracker showed it to be hitting the stumps.
On the pads of Wade, he works it towards deep backward square leg and takes three as the fielders do the mop up job.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Beautiful shot by Smith! This was full and on middle and leg, he just comes on the front foot and drives this down the down the ground through mid on for a boundary.
On the pads of Wade to start the fresh over by Curran. He whips it behind square leg and takes a brace.
Gets the line right this time. This one is in the channel. Wade lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Wade is right behind the line to block off the back foot.
Full ball on off this time, Wade punches this straight to mid on.
Fuller ball on middle this time, Wade tucks it towards the mid-wicket region with ease.
Fullish ball, this is on the fifth stump line. Wade shoulders arms to this one.
Good length around off, Smith works it behind square leg and gets off strike.

FOUR! Crunched! Shortish ball outside off, Wade has room to cash in. He stays back and hammers the cut through point. Woakes continues bowling the wayward lines and lengths. Australia trail by 180 now.
Goes fuller on the pads this time, Wade flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, Wade taps it towards cover.
On the pads again, Wade pushes this towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Good length around off, Smith blocks it towards mid on. 6 runs from the over, without a hint of trouble.
Floated outside off, pushed towards the man at cover.
Another one floated on off, Wade comes down the track trying to negate the spin. He flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Floated on the pads, Smith pushes this towards mid on and takes a single.

Close one this! Leach bowls this one in the rough, gets a lot of turn off the surface. Wade tries to work it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball loops up but goes wide of the short leg to his left.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Wade comes down the track and pushes the ball towards mid on and keeps strike.
Good length ball on middle and off, Wade looks to work it towards the leg side but it goes off the leading edge towards cover.
Down the leg side, Wade tries to flick but misses.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! LBW! Matthew Wade is now gone and as always, the lone standing warrior is Steven Smith who is playing at the other end. Curran comes steaming in and bowls this one on the middle and off. There is a hint of late inward movement as it hits the surface. Wade looks to flick this one towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits Wade on the front pad and the English players appeal. Kumar Dharmasena takes his time and raises the dreaded finger. Wade goes for the review straightaway. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge shows no bat. The Ball Tracker comes into play and this one is CLIPPING the leg pole. Umpire's call it is and thus, Australia retain their review. Sam Curran picks up his first Ashes wicket and he will be delighted. Australia 4 down and they trail by 176.
Swing and a miss! Full ball just outside off, Marsh goes for the drive off the first ball but misses it completely. Not the approach that the visitors would want from him right now.
Marsh defends it from within the crease. End of a successful over for Curran.
Loopy ball on middle, Smith pushes this towards long on for a single.
Floated one around off and middle, Marsh pushes it towards cover.

Huge appeal but looks to be going down. England do not review. Floats this one around middle as Marsh looks to work it towards mid on. He is late into the shot and is hit on the pads. Huge appeal from Leach and other English players but nothing from the umpire. The Ball Tracker rolls in and confirms the same - going down indeed.
Floated fuller ball this time, pushed towards mid on by Marsh this time.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter around off this time, Marsh looks to work it towards point but this goes off the outside edge towards the slip cordon, along the ground. A good end to the over from Leach.
Length ball just outside off, Smith pushes this one off the back foot towards extra cover.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards the man at mid-wicket.
This time fuller and near the boot, Smith flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a single.
Just ahead of a good length, Marsh solidly defends this one towards silly mid off.
On the pads of Marsh, he flicks it towards deep backward square leg as the batters take two. Marsh is off the mark with this couple.
Again on the pads, Marsh flicks it towards square leg and takes another couple.
Shorter this time way outside off, Smith pushes this one wide of the fielder at gully who dives to his right as the batters take a couple.
Floated outside off, Smith pushes this one towards cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
This time floated on middle and leg, Smith blocks it out.

SIX! 10TH TEST FIFTY IN A ROW FOR STEVEN SMITH! Is this a purple patch or is it just the class of the man? We think the latter! This one is tossed up on middle and off, Smith comes down the track and heaves this over long on for a maximum. Gets to his 27th Test fifty in style! Also, he now owns the record for the most consecutive 50-plus scores against a single Test team. Records just keep tumbling at his feet. Majestic!
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Good length ball on middle and off, Marsh pushes it towards mid off.
This time fuller by Curran, Marsh pushes it towards the man at cover.
A very low full toss outside off, Marsh tries to bring his bat down in time but fails to do so as the ball carries through to Bairstow.

Fumble and another run! This is wide outside off, Marsh opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man. The batters take off as Burns hares after it. He collects it near the ropes but fumbles and that allows the third which brings Steven Smith on strike.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Good running! On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a quick couple. The Australians are alert here as the hosts look tired.
Full and on off by Broad to start off, Marsh pushes it towards mid off.
Again full and outside off, Marsh does not fiddle with it.
Down the leg side, Marsh looks to flick with just one hand on the bat but misses. It kisses his pad outside the leg pole and goes to the left of Bairstow who does well to pouch it.
Short and wide outside off, Marsh looks to cut with a wild swing but misses it completely.
Fuller this time, driven towards mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Powerful stroke by Smith! Full and on off, Smith drives this one through mid off and straight to the fence.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and gets a single to get off strike.
Full to Marsh, he punches it towards mid on.
Another fuller one, Marsh again punches it down the ground.
On the pads of Marsh, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Outside off by Curran to Smith, he leaves it alone.
Full ball outside off, Marsh goes for a drive towards the cover region but it goes off the inner half back towards the bowler.
On middle and leg, Marsh tucks this one towards square leg.
Again on middle and leg, Marsh pushes this one towards mid on.
Similar line, Marsh plays it towards mid-wicket all along the ground.

FOUR! Bad ball by Broad, releasing all the pressure! Short and wide outside off, Marsh gets onto the back foot and cuts this one square through point where there is no protection and the ball races to the fence.
Length ball on middle and off, Marsh pushes this one back towards mid on. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Starts with a bumper which is too high. Smith ducks under it.
A good bouncer this time. Banged on middle and off, Smith looks to duck under it but then decides to go for the pull. He can't get bat on ball though.
Another back of a length ball but this one is sliding down the leg side. Smith lets this one go.
Goes for the good length ball around off, Smith lets it be.

In the air... but safe. Another bouncer on middle. Smith this time stands tall and goes for the pull but can't find the timing. The ball balloons high in the air but lands in the vacant region behind square leg. They take a run, first one off the session.
Fuller around off, pushed back to the mid off fielder. A testing over this one from Archer.
Good length ball on the off pole, Smith clips it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Brilliant timing and no one is stopping that one. Broad goes fuller outside off, Marsh gets into the act as he leans into the drive and crunches the cover drive to the fence. A top shop that one.

A muted appeal but this looked going down the leg side. This is landed on a good length around middle and leg, Marsh fails to put bat on ball as this shapes a hint in to hit him on the pads. The ball goes towards square leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Fuller on the pads this time, tucked towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly fullish length, Marsh blunts it towards the off side.
Length ball around off, Marsh taps it towards point and takes a run.
Fuller ball around off, pushed towards mid off.
Bouncer! A good one as well as this caught Marsh in two minds. This was landed on middle. He first wanted to pull it away but decided against it.
Good length around off, Marsh pushes it towards cover solidly.
Fuller again, Marsh drives it firmly but finds the extra cover fielder.
Bouncer this time. Marsh ducks under it.
Good length ball that bounces a bit extra off the pitch. Marsh awkwardly pushes it towards gully with soft hands.
Good length ball around off, pushed back to the bowler by Smith.

FOUR! Easy picking this for Smith. Broad overpitches this outside off, Smith leans into the shot and times his cover drive. The cover fielder chases the ball but can't get there before the ball touches the fence.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Bouncer! What was that? Back of a length ball, Smith ducks under it. As the ball goes past Smith, it shapes away from Bairstow who gets his right hand out in time to pouch this one.
Another bouncer but the line is not right as this goes down the leg side. Smith ducks under it.
Yorker to end the over. But again, Smith gets his bat down in time to dig it out.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Marsh.
Looks to bowl a yorker but dishes a full toss. Marsh can't give it a proper treatment and pushes this towards mid on.
A ball in the channel this time, Marsh covers his timber and lets it go to Bairstow.

OUT! Marsh has thrown it away! He can't believe it! Archer can, number four for him. Archer bangs another shortish ball around middle and leg. Marsh looks to pull but the ball takes the top half of the bat and goes straight in the hands of Jack Leach at fine leg. Australia trail by 134 runs with half their side back in the hut. Smith, however, continues to battle from one end.

Huge appeal! Archer appeals. He wants five. Umpire is unmoved. He begs for the review to his skipper. Root is not interested though. This is a good length ball and is angled into the batter. Paine looks to work it down the leg side but he is late in the shot and is hit on the pads. A good call eventually from the skipper as the Ultra Edge confirms there was an inside edge on that one.
Back of a length around off, tapped towards point. Eventful over comes to an end.
Great fielding by Broad! Curran starts off with a loosener, full and wide outside off. Smith pushes it wide of mid off. Broad runs to his left and puts in a dive to stop the ball.
Good length ball on middle and off, Smith shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Down the leg side, Smith tries to flick this one but misses.
Outside off, left alone by Smith.
Another one outside off, Smith shoulders arms to let that one through.

DROPPED! Oh dear! What has Joe Root done here? Steven Smith is literally the last man in the universe whose catch you want to drop right now but Root has indeed put it down. Curran bowls this one short of a length outside off, trying to make Smith play at this one. He obliges and tries to upper cut it over the slip cordon. However, he does not get the best connection on it and it goes high between first and second slip fielders. Joe Root at first slip jumps high and to his right, gets two hands to it but puts it down. Smith is dropped on 66 and he gets a life. A very good news for Australia but not so much for England.
Good length ball outside off, Paine lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly shorter but down the leg side. Paine is not bothered and allows the keeper to collect.

Back of a length ball on middle, Paine goes for the pull and manages to roll his wrists on this one. It goes towards square leg for a single. He is off the mark with that one. The shortish ball has troubled him this series but he did well there.
Length ball around off, tapped onto the pitch on the off side by Smith.
Another good bouncer! Smith looked to duck under it but maybe it kissed the helmet as it went into the gloves of Bairstow.
FIVE WIDES! Bangs a short ball again but this is down the leg side and it is too high as Smith ducks. Bairstow can't collect this one either.
Another bouncer! Smith sways away from it. A good over from Archer this one.

Another LBW shout but again looks to be going down the leg side. Root is not going for the review again. Fullish length ball angled into Paine who looks to work it down the leg side but is late into the shot again. He is hit on the pads as Curran appeals. A good decision from the umpire as this pitched outside leg which was confirmed by the Ball Tracker.
On the stumps on a good length. Paine is solid in his block this time.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads on a fuller length, Paine finds the square leg fielder with his flick.
Length ball around off this time, blocked by Paine on the off side.
Beaten! A good nut to finish the over. Curran pitches it around off and makes it go past the outside edge of Paine's drive. Lucky not to edge that one.

In the air...but safe. Good length ball around off, Smith shuffles and looks to work it down the leg side but the ball takes the leading edge and balloon towards the vacant silly point region. Lucky escape this one.

A beauty from Archer! What a ripper this one! Smith hasn't been beaten this comprehensively one can say. This is on a fuller length and closer to the off pole. Smith can't leave it. No one can. He looks to push but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. The battle between the two is on says the commentator on air.
Slightly shortish length, Smith stands tall to push it towards point.
On middle on a good length, tucked towards mid-wicket by Smith this time.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Bangs this short but down the leg side. Smith is not bothered.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards mid off by Paine.
Beaten! Testing line this one from Curran to Paine. Pitches around off and makes it shape away from the prod of Paine. Lucky not to edge that one.
Slightly shorter around off, Paine stands tall to block it towards point.

OUT! Caught behind! Curran has his man. Wicket number two for him and Paine can't do much in this innings as he walks back to the pavilion. Sam pitches this slightly fuller and makes Paine go for the drive. He sets him up nicely by mixing his variations. This one is a scrambled seam delivery and nips away on landing. Paine goes to push it down the ground with a straight bat but the away movement means the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Bairstow. Smith is running out of partners here.

OUT! LBW! Two in two for Curran. That looked plumb. And the third umpire agrees as well. Curran pitches this one fuller on middle and leg. The ball swings back in and beats the defensive bat of Cummins. It's rapped on the pads, huge appeal follows and the umpire agrees. Cummins, however goes for the review after consulting Smith at the other end. Will that help? Let's see. Nothing on the Ultra Edge. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Well, it is hitting the timber and Cummins will have to walk back. Dead duck. Australia in deep trouble as wicket number 7 goes down. They trail by 128 runs. Our ever alert fellow commentator pings me - 'In the first innings, Cummins got Curran LBW but overstepped. Sam has not returned the favour!' Sharp memory.

FOUR! No hat-trick for Curran! He attempts for a yorker but dishes a full toss around the fifth stump line. Siddle manages to put bat and ball and gets it away past the slip cordon for a boundary. End of a stupendous over by Curran, a very impactful one, two wickets and 4 runs off it.
FOUR! Short of a length ball outside off, Smith stands tall and punches this through backward point for a boundary. This man does not seem concerned as to what is happening at the other end.

Another short of a length ball, Smith comes down the track but has to defend it in the end. It hits the splice of the bat and falls onto the pitch. Smith initially does not know where the ball is but finds it out later.
Smith has defended this length ball on middle from within the crease.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky, lucky, Steven Smith! This is a fuller ball outside off, Smith looks to open the face of his bat and guide this to the right of the fielder at gully. He does not get the proper connection on it and the ball goes between the second and third slip fielders through to the third man fence.
Smith defends it from within the crease. They pick up a single.
Siddle has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles to block but this goes towards the off side off the outer half of his bat.
Fuller ball on middle, Smith is right behind the line of the ball to block.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith looks to work it down the leg side but he is late into the shot. He misses and the ball hits the pads. This was going down the leg side and hence the muted appeal.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball outside off, Smith plays inside the line and it shapes away to go away from the outside edge of his bat.
Bouncer to finish the over. However, this one is going down the leg side. Smith lets it be.
Left alone on a length by Siddle. A good length ball, angled into the right-hander. Siddle covers the stumps and allows the keeper to collect it behind the wicket.
This one slides down the leg side. Bairstow dives to his left to stop but can't gather it cleanly. They take a bye.
Ohh! Smith wants to hammer this one through covers. This is pitched on a good length and shapes away as Smith looks too heave this  away. The ball goes past the flashing blade to the keeper.
A bumper to follow! Smith does well to evade.
And another bouncer on middle, Smith this time stands tall to push it towards gully and get off strike.
Good length ball on the pads, tucked towards short fine leg by Siddle to get a run. This has been a superb spell from Archer.
Fuller ball outside off, Siddle shoulders arms to this one.
On middle this time, blocked towards mid on by Siddle.
Fuller ball on the pads, Siddle timed it well but can't beat the mid-wicket fielder.

Huge appeal for an lbw but the umpire says not out. Curran wasn't too sure either after the umpire's decision as he looked to his skipper. Goes for the fuller ball, Siddle misses his flick and is hit on the pads. A good ball but equally a good call by the bowler and the skipper not to review as the Ball Tracker shows this was pitching outside leg.
This time Siddle is solid behind the block.

Curran has rapped Siddle in front of the stumps again on a fullish length. Siddle again misses his flick and is hit flush on the pads. Again, this looked going down the leg side. The appeal has been denied by the umpire, and a good decision that. England don't review again and rightly so. The Ball Tracker showed that this was pitched in line but was missing the leg pole. Another good over from Curran.
Floats one on a fullish length, pushed towards mid-wicket by Smith.

Flatter one around off and on a shortish length, Smith looks to cut but can't get the timing right. The ball goes through point and Smith calls for a quick couple. The fielder from deep point throws the ball towards the non-striker's end but Siddle is well in as Leach breaks the stumps.
Tossed up ball on middle, Smith pushes this towards cover for a run.
Another tossed up ball, negotiated well by Siddle.
This one is flatter around off, Siddle does well to block off the back foot.
Tossed up ball to finish the over. Siddle blocks it out off the front foot.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, Smith flicks it towards square leg and wants a couple. But the deep square leg fielder hares at the ball and keeps it to one.
Good length ball outside off, Siddle lets it be.
Fullish ball around off, Siddle finds the mid off fielder with his drive.
Goes past the outside edge this time. Curran pitches this slightly fuller and makes it shape away from the right-hander. Siddle tries to push inside the line and misses.
Goes for the yorker but dishes out a full toss around off, Siddle pushes this through point to cross over for a run.
Shortish ball around middle and off, Smith throws his bat at it as he looks to loft it over the slip cordon. Can't get bat on the ball though.
Darted onto the off pole, Siddle pushes it back towards the bowler.
Leach tosses it up, Siddle pushes it towards the off side.
Tossed up on middle and off, pushed towards mid off by Siddle.
Flighted on middle, Siddle blocks it out.
Similar line, Siddle does the same thing and pushes it back towards Leach.
6 balls, 6 dots from Leach. Full and floated on middle, Leach blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Finally Steven Smith is dismissed and Chris Woakes is the man to do it. A very fine innings from Smith comes to an end and without him, the visitors' score would have looked a paltry one. Good length ball just outside off, it comes inside with the angle after landing. Smith shuffles across in his usual manner, trying to flick the ball towards the leg side but unusually, he misses his flick this time and is hit on the pads. He is caught dead in front of the stumps. The English players appeal and umpire Erasmus raises his finger straightaway. Steven Smith has a talk with Peter Siddle at the other end and he advises him against taking the review. Wise decision as the Ball Tracker shows three reds. Australia still trail by another 107 runs with just 2 wickets in hand.

Jaffa from Woakes first up to Lyon and he is beaten. On a length, just outside off, it pitches and swings away. Lyon looks to defend but does so inside the line and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Lyon goes for the off side push this time but he edges it wide of the slip cordon and the ball races towards the third man fence.
On the leg side, Lyon looks to flick but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
On the pads, Lyon tucks it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Good shot by Lyon this time and the deficit is below 100 now. Good length ball outside off, Lyon caresses this one through point for a boundary.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fuller this time outside off, Siddle gets on the front foot and punches this one through cover. Curran hares after it and keeps it just in the field as the batters take three.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Lyon.
Another length ball, this time on middle and leg, played down onto the pitch.
Bouncer this time, Lyon looks to upper cut it over the slip cordon but misses the ball.
On the off side, fuller ball. Lyon blocks it off.
Full and wide outside off, Siddle gets onto the front foot and punches this one towards the cover region. The fielders hare after it as the batters take three.
Length ball on middle and leg, punched off the back foot by the batsman towards mid on.
Lyon pushes this good length ball straight back towards Woakes.
Down the leg side, Lyon looks to flick but misses.
Play and a miss! This time Lyon looks to defend off the back foot but he does so inside the line and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Swing and a miss this time! Short and wide outside off, Lyon goes after it with a wild slash and misses.
Good length ball on middle and off, Siddle looks to work this one towards the leg side but gets a leading edge which goes to cover-point.
Siddle defends this length ball off the back foot onto the ground.
Yorker by Archer this time, Siddle jams it out.
FOUR! Valuable runs for the Aussies! Short and wide outside off, Siddle cuts this one through cover-point for a boundary. The trail now down to 89 runs.
Bouncer this time on middle and leg, Siddle ducks under it.
Peter shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball on the fourth stump line, it pitches and nips away. Lyon looks to defend but is squared up as the ball goes to Bairstow behind the wickets.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Lyon.

FOUR! Good length ball on off, Lyon stays back and lofts it over mid off for a boundary. It crosses the fence on a couple of bounces. He was expecting the short ball and that might have helped him play that stroke so well. The partnership moves on to 22 runs and the run rate of it is above 5. Counterattack is on!
Full on middle and leg, driven through mid-on by the batsman.

SIX! Pulled away by Lyon and into the crowd! This is again short in length and on middle, he just swings his bat at it and the ball flies towards the square leg region for a maximum. Lyon playing some extravagant strokes here.
Nathan has punched that ball through the offside. 10 from the over, this stand is eating down the deficit quite quickly.
Fullish length ball around off, Siddle strokes it through point to take a single.
Bouncer but down the leg side. Bairstow leaps towards his left to pouch that one and save a certain boundary.

FOUR! Up and over! Lyon having some fun in the middle now. Archer pitches this fuller, in the slot for Lyon. The batsman stays in the crease and lifts it over the cover-point for a boundary. He is playing a little gem here for Australia.
Shortish ball around off, Lyon wants to upper cut this one as he his the man with confidence. Can't get bat to the ball.

DROPPED! Short ball on middle and leg, Lyon again looks to pull this one over square leg but gets a top edge on it. The ball skies towards backward square leg, Leach goes to his left as he tries to take the catch. He settles himself under it, gets both his hands on it but puts down the catch. That was a dolly and he should have hung onto it. Archer cannot get his 5-fer yet and in the meanwhile, Lyon takes a single and reaches the 1000 run milestone in Test matches. Lucky!
Bumper down the leg side. Siddle ducks under it.
Flatter ball on the leg stump. Lyon sits down to sweep but misses the timing.
Another flighted ball on the leg pole line, Lyon sweeps it towards deep square leg for a run.
A sweep from Siddle this time. A tossed up ball on middle, Siddle sweeps for a run.
Another sweep but finds the short fine leg fielder this time.
And again. But again can't beat the short fine leg fielder. Leach continues tossing the ball on middle and leg.

Connects the sweep well this time and gets a single off the last ball to keep the strike with him. Tossed up ball around middle and leg, Lyon sweeps towards deep square leg with ease. Not a very good over this one from Leach.

OUT! TIMBER! 5-fer for Archer and the fun for Lyon has ended! Archer steams in to start his new over, Lyon must be expecting the short ball but Archer surprises him with a knuckle-ball-yorker. It loops on him, coming in. Lyon misses the ball altogether as he looks to swing it away. The stumps are destroyed and the good looking partnership of 37 runs has ended for the visitors.

Dropped or not? Looked like that had hit Hazlewood on the glove but the replays show that it has hit him on the grille of the helmet. However, the umpire has given it as runs so Hazlewood is off the mark. Bouncer by Archer to Hazlewood, he looks to fend at it but misses. The ball comes off the grille of the helmet and goes to the right of Root at first slip. It hits him on his forearm as he dives and rolls behind as the batters take one. Initially it looked like Root had dropped another catch but fortunately for him, that is not the case.
Down the leg side, Siddle goes after it but misses his flick.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

OUT! A blinder from Rory Burns at gully to close out the Australian innings! Number 6 for Archer, his second 6-fer in the series! Fuller length ball around off this time from Archer, Siddle throws his bat at the ball but it takes the outside edge. It hurries to the right of Rory Burns at gully who dives full length to gobble the catch. A top performance from Archer this one and he is receiving a rousing applause from the crowd. AUSTRALIA ALL OUT FOR 225!
Short of a length ball to start the innings by Cummins. It is very close to the body of Burns and he does well to evade it.

FOUR LEG BYES! Proper bouncer this time on middle and leg, Burns initially looks to play at it but then pulls away. He tries to duck under it but is late in doing so. The ball goes off his shoulder over Tim Paine and into the fine leg fence.

NASTY! Another great bumper by Cummins and this one has hit Burns on the helmet. Bouncer on middle and off, Burns looks to sway away this time straightaway but the ball shoots off the surface. It hits his glove first and then onto the grille of the helmet. The ball falls onto the pitch and umpire Erasmus straightaway signals to the dressing room for the physio.
Bouncer on middle again by Cummins, this time Burns does well to evade it.
Full and wide outside off, Paine dives to his right as the ball shapes further away after crossing the batter. He pouches it nicely.

Beaten! Superb last ball to finish the over by Cummins. Pitches this on a good length and closer to the off stump. Burns looks to play at it but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. No wickets in the over but a top one to say the least.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked by Denly off the back foot.
Fuller on middle and off, Denly blocks it off the front foot this time.
Length ball wide outside off, Denly looks to play at it but does so inside the line of the delivery.
Front foot defense offered by Denly to this full ball on middle and off.
Solid defense by Denly once more as he defends it from within the crease.
On the pads of Denly, he tucks it towards the square leg region. Maiden to start off for Hazlewood.
Short of a length ball just outside off, Burns sways away from it.
The plan looks clear for Burns. Bowl as many bouncers as you can to him and that is what Cummins is doing. Another bumper on the leg pole line and Burns ducks under it.
Short of a length just outside off, Burns evades this one as well.
Bowls a surprise full delivery. Burns is up for it and pushes it back towards Cummins. Good contest going on here between the two.
Pulls his length back again does Cummins, he leaves this one alone.
Bouncer again! Burns ducks under this one and has a nervous smile on his face following the short ball. End of another over by Cummins. England remain unscathed.
Denly prods forward and tries to block this one off the front foot but gets a leading edge towards mid-wicket.
Joe Denly shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

DROPPED! This was exactly what the visitors would not have wanted going into Stumps at Day 2 but Harris has put this one down. This one was full and wide outside off, Denly is lured into this one. He goes for the drive and gets a thick outside edge on it. It goes straight to Harris at gully, at chest height. He tries to take it with his fingers pointing up but it pops out and goes behind for a run. Denly has been dismissed in similar fashion throughout this series and the edge should not have come as a shock to Harris at gully. However, Harris is now seen to be running back to the dressing room after getting hurt while he dropped the catch. Wow, physical as well as mental harm!
Bouncer by Hazlewood to Burns, he ducks in time and lets it through to Paine.
FOUR! Down the leg side, Burns flicks this one off his pads and towards fine leg for a boundary. He is off the mark with that.

NOT OUT! ENGLAND REMAIN UNSCATHED! This always looked to be pitching outside leg to the naked eye and the Ball Tracker confirms it. Hazlewood bowls one on a good length around leg, it straightens a touch after pitching. Burns looks to flick it off his pads towards the leg side but misses it and is hit high on the pads. The Australian players appeal loudly following the miss and umpire Dharmasena agrees as he raises his finger. However, Burns is convinced that he is not out and straightaway signals the 'T'. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracker comes into play and shows that this has pitched outside leg. Successful review for England and they head into STUMPS ON DAY 2 at 9/0, leading by 78 runs.
Uppish but wide of Wade. Fuller one on the pads to start the day from Cummins. Denly flicks it off his pads and past the short leg fielder for a couple. First runs off the day.
Fuller but this one is around off, Denly blocks it out back to the bowler.
FOUR! Glorious drive! Cummins goes fuller again, Denly caresses the drive past the mid off fielder and the ball races to the fence. First boundary of the day.
In the channel outside off, Denly thought to have a poke but the away movement meant he dropped his hands and let the ball through to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Denly wants to work it down the leg side but misses his flick to get hit on the pads.
Slightly fullish on middle, pushed towards mid on this time. Cummins would probably want to get closer to the off pole in his next over.
Shortish length on middle and leg, Burns stands tall to block this one onto the pitch on the leg side.

Huge appeal for a caught behind down the leg side but the umpire says not out. Australia don't opt for the review. This is another back of a length ball which is going down the leg side. Burns looks to glance it fine down the leg side but misses. Paine dives to his right to pouch it and goes for the appeal. No edge, confirms the Ultra Edge.
Fuller on off and middle, blocked nicely by Burns.
Bumper but again sprayed down the leg side. Burns lets it be.
Good length ball on middle this time. Burns is solid with his block.
FOUR! Hammered over point! Wide outside off on a good length. Burns has enough room to flex his arms. He gets in position and hammers it over point to get his first boundary of the day.
Good length ball outside off, Denly lets it be.
Around off on a good length, blocked this time.
Hit on the body! Cummins goes for the back of a length ball, Denly wants to sway away but the ball doesn't bounce and hits Denly on the back. The ball rolls towards fine leg and they take a leg bye.
Goes around the wicket and bangs the ball short in the channel. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball outside off this time, Burns shoulders arms again.
Goes for the yorker but this one is a low full toss, it's jammed out nicely by Burns.
Around off on a good length, Denly is solid with the block.
Fuller ball around off and middle, Denly keeps it out.
Good length ball around the fourth stump line this time. Denly lets it pass to the keeper behind the wicket.
Beaten! A good nut that one. Pitches on a good length and shapes away from the push of Denly. Very close to taking the outside edge on that one.
Another ball in the channel from Hazlewood, Denly this time is not lured into it and shoulders arms.
Good length ball outside off, Denly pushes this towards gully. Maiden!
Good length ball around middle, Burns works it down the leg side but can't go past the short leg fielder.
Good work from Paine to save a certain boundary. Bouncer but this one goes way down the leg side. Paine leaps to his right to pouch that one.
Around middle and off, Burns is solid in defense this time.

FOUR! Glamorous! That is a super shot! Cummins dishes this fuller around off, Burns leans into the drive and creams this one through covers to the fence. He has had his fair share of trouble with the bouncers but anything fuller, Burns has not missed out. Also, he hasn't been rattled by the barrage of bouncers he has received. Nasser Hussain on air quips that Rory is not thinking about the deliveries that has gone by and living in the present. Quickly forgetting, that's the key as a batsman, especially if you are an opener.

Good comeback from Cummins! Bangs it short around off, Burns looks to take the bat away but is late into it. As he takes the bat away, the ball takes the toe end and goes towards the slip cordon on the bounce.
Another bouncer from Cummins. Burns does well to get out of the way of it.
Beaten! A beauty to start the fresh over from Hazlewood. Slightly shortish around off, Denly has a poke but the ball goes past the outside edge. Lucky not to edge that one.
Beaten again! Another beauty from Hazlewood. Denly has another poke to this good length ball around off, but it whizzes past the outside edge.
A solid defense from Denly this time.
Good length ball around off again, Denly guides this towards the gully fielder by opening the face of the bat. The gully fielder dives to his right and parries the ball towards point.
Bouncer but this one is going down. Denly ducks under it.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Just behind good length around off, Burns lets it be.
Bouncer on middle, Burns ducks under it.
Good length ball on the pads, pushed toward mid on.
Another bumper! Burns sways away nicely. He drops his hands in time and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Slightly fullish length, Burns pushes this gently towards mid off to take a run.
Good length ball on the pads, Denly looks to flick but can't get bat on ball. The ball hits the pads and rolls towards short leg.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Rory stands tall and blocks.
On middle this time on a good length, Burns pushes this towards point to take a run.
On middle and off, blocked by Denly with ease.
Slightly fuller around off, Denly looks to block it towards the off side but the ball goes towards the short leg fielder off the inner half of the willow.
Slightly fuller, Denly drives it to the left of the bowler but Wade dives to his right to stop the ball, can't gather it cleanly but no runs.
Around off on a good length, Denly taps it towards point.
Floated ball on middle, Burns works it towards fine leg and takes one.
Around off, Denly comes down the track to smash it but finds the mid on fielder.
Goes fuller and offers a lot of loop. Can't beat the mid-wicket fielder this time.
Flatter one around off, worked towards the off side.

FOUR! Over the bowler's head! Loopy ball around off and middle, Denly walks down the track and lifts it over Lyon's head and to the long off fence. Superb shot. The lead now is 100. Also, this boundary brings up the highest opening stand in this Ashes for either side.

SIX! Denly doesn't want Lyon to get settled. Another loopy ball around middle and leg. Denly again dances down the track and pummels this one over the long on fence for a maximum. Daddy Denly is looking in good touch in the middle. Seems the newborn has brought some confidence in the right-hander. 11 from the over!
Siddle starts with a ball around off on a good length, Burns blocks it out.
Another ball around off, Burns pushes this towards square leg and takes a run.
Good length ball around off, Denly looks to block it on the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller one this time. Denly pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off this time. Denly drives this one through cover-point and takes three before the fielder can return the ball. He is looking very positive out in the middle.
On middle, Burns blocks it out off the back foot.
Loopy ball on middle, Denly works it down the leg side.
Flatter one down the leg side this time. Denly goes for the flick but misses.
Slightly shorter around off, Denly pushes this towards cover.
FOUR! Denly in punishing mode! Another loopy ball around off, Denly has his dancing shoes on to drill this one right of the mid off fielder. The ball races to the fence in a jiffy.
Flighted around off, Denly blocks this one out with ease.
Darts this one on middle, Denly gets to the pitch of the ball to block.

FOUR LEG BYES! Poor line from Siddle this time. Runs coming thick and fast at the moment for England. Siddle sprays this down the leg side. Burns looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits the pads and goes towards the fine leg fence.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Back of a length ball, angled into the batter. Burns stands tall to tap it towards point.

On middle and leg and on a good length this time. Burns can't get bat on ball again and is hit on the pads. Siddle got a couple of fielding changes after the last ball as he got a slip added but this line is not what he would've liked to bowl.

FOUR! Siddle bowls a fullish ball around off, Burns drives it straight down the ground and to the long off fence. 50 up for  England with that exquisite drive. That went between the legs of Denly at the non-striker's end.
Good length around off, blocked out easily by Burns.
Tossed up just outside off, Denly looks to push it towards the leg side but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Another one tossed up outside off, Denly this time does manage to push it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! The opening stand has been broken and it's Lyon who has provided the breakthrough. Not a wicket taking delivery though. This one is shorter and outside off and stays a bit low too. Burns looks to cut it through point but gets a bottom edge on that one and Tim Paine does well to hold onto it behind the wickets. Burns was looking good out in the middle but he has thrown his wicket away. He looks distraught. Australia will be hoping that this wicket is the opening that they need to get back in the game as the hosts are still effectively 123/1.
Flatter on the pads, Root works it through square leg to take a couple and get off the mark.
On the pads and on a fullish length, Root works it towards the mid-wicket region to take a quick single.
Darted one on the pads of Denly, he works it fine down the leg side to take a run. A successful over by Lyon where he picked the first wicket in this Test.
Outside off on a good length, Denly lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller around off, Denly strokes it towards cover.
Good length ball around off this time, Denly works it towards the gully fielder with soft hands.
Bouncer this time. Denly ducks under it.
In the channel on a slightly fuller length. Denly lets it go.
Good length ball around off, Denly blocks it solidly. A maiden over after a while.
Length ball just outside off, Root pushes this one towards point with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Bouncer by Cummins to Denly on middle and leg, Denly ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Joe Denly.
Another one, similar line and length, Denly shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another length ball on a similar line, this time Denly does go for the block but edges it. It goes towards the man at gully on the bounce.
Bouncer down the leg side, Denly ducks under it and lets Paine collect it behind the stumps.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Root.

FOUR! Up and over the slip cordon! Did Root mean to play it that fine? Only he will know but anyway he has got the desired result. Short and wide outside off, Root goes onto the back foot and tries to upper cut it but gets a faint top edge on it. The ball flies over the slip cordon and goes to the third man fence.
Length ball just outside off, Root looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Root shoulders arms to let that one through.
Fuller this time outside off, Root leans into the drive and pushes this one towards the cover region. The man in the deep mops it up and the batters take two.
Good length ball on off pole, Root blocks it out.
Full and wide just outside off, pushed towards the man at short extra cover.
This time a bit shorter in length, pushed off the back foot towards the same region.
Good length ball outside off, Denly pushes this towards point.
Similar length, on the off pole line, Denly pushes this towards mid on.
Slapped away towards cover! Short and wide outside off, Denly plays this one on the up and slaps it towards the cover region. The batters take two while the fielder does the mopping up job.
OUCH! That has hit Denly on the box and he is down on the ground! Good length ball around off, it jags back in. Denly tries to block but misses to get hit on the box. Looks in a lot of pain.

EDGED BUT SHORT! Good length ball around off, it nips away after pitching. Root looks to defend it with soft hands but gets an outside edge on it as the ball goes towards first slip on the bounce. Warner gets a hand on it but it goes past him towards the third man fence and the batters take two. Almost the 8th time Josh had Root there in Tests!
Length ball outside off, Root pushes this towards point and takes a single.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Good length ball on middle and leg, blocked towards mid on this time.
Denly looks to block this good length ball around off but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Denly presents the full face of the bat and defends it off the front foot.
Length ball around off, blocked towards cover.
This time on middle and leg, Root pushes this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

Good fielding! This is fuller and around off, exactly where Denly wants it to be. He drives at it and the ball goes to the left of mid off. Siddle runs from mid off and dives to his left as he saves at least a couple of runs for his side. Good effort from the bowler.
Bouncer down the leg side, Denly ducks under it.
FOUR! Length ball around middle and off, Denly looks to push at it but gets an inside edge on it. It goes past the leg pole and into the fine leg fence for a boundary. Lucky for Denly.
Length ball on middle and leg, Denly blocks this one out.
Starts with a fuller ball around off, Root pushes it straight down the ground but can't beat the mid off fielder.
FOUR! Whipped! On the pads this time. Root flicks it through square leg to earn a boundary. Easy picking that one.

Run out chance? Well, not really, Denly was in but anyway, Wade couldn't hit the timber with the throw either. Root drives this fuller ball towards cover and wants a run then denies. Denly has come a long way and he has to return. He gets back in time though.
Solid block to this ball around off.
Beaten! Late movement on that one. Pitches around off and lets it shape away from the bat of Root. It whizzes past the outside edge and to the keeper.
This one is on middle and off, has kept a bit low as well. Root does well to block.
Length ball just around off, it jags back in sharply and hits Denly on the thigh pad as he misses his block. Siddle exchanges a stare with Denly.
Denly has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Denly looks to push at this one straight down the ground but it goes off the outer half towards the empty third man region for a boundary. The boundary takes the English lead to 152.
This time Denly plays this one towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Denly again looks to push this one down the ground but it goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Length ball coming into Denly, he misses his flick and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full and outside off, Root pushes it towards mid off.
On middle and off, Root blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Root pushes this one towards point and takes one.
On the pads of Denly, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single to give his skipper the strike.
Full length ball outside off, pushed towards cover-point.
Length ball just outside off, Root pushes this one off the back foot towards deep point and takes a couple to end the over.
Length ball on middle and leg, Denly pushes it towards mid on off the back foot.
This time just outside off, Denly tries to block it out off the back foot but it goes off the inside half onto the pitch.
Denly blocks this one off the back foot.
Fuller in length this time, pushed towards mid off.
Length ball just outside off, Denly pushes this towards cover-point.
Another length ball, blocked out by Denly. Maiden by Siddle, trying to pile on the pressure.
Tossed up wide outside off, Root blocks this one out.

OUT! CAUGHT! The English skipper is out of here and this is the 7th time that Lyon has dismissed Root, the joint-most with his teammates, Cummins and Hazlewood. This delivery is nothing special from Lyon, just like his last wicket. He pitches this one way outside off and gets it to spin back in a little. Root goes far too ahead in an attempt to put bat on ball but gets an outside edge instead on it which goes straight to Smith at first slip. He won't drop those. England are effectively 156/2 and Lyon is the man with both the wickets until now. Root's mediocre Ashes with the bat comes to a close.
Tossed up wide and outside off, Stokes blocks it out.
Again Lyon tosses it up, Stokes blocks it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Ohh! Almost another one for Lyon! He pitches this one a touch shorter on the off pole line and it skids through after landing. Stokes goes onto the back foot to block it out. He gets an outside edge on it to keep it out, luckily for him. Had he missed that, he was plumb LBW.
Sprays this one down the leg side. Denly lets it be.
Fuller one around off, pushed towards mid off by Denly this time.
Another ball on off and middle, Denly is solid with the block again.
Good length ball around off, tapped towards cover by Denly.

Good ball that one. Where did that hit? High on the thigh pad it seems. This one jagged back in with the angle from a good length ball. Denly looks to work it down the leg side but misses to get high on the pads.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Darted onto the leg pole line, Stokes looks to flick this one but misses. It kisses his pads and goes towards fine leg as the batters take a leg bye.
Tossed up and wide outside off,  Denly defends it out.
Denly comes down the track and pushes this one back towards Lyon.
This time Denly stays back in his crease and pushes it back towards Lyon again.
Denly pushes this flighted ball off the front foot towards mid on.

Tossed up outside off, Denly tries to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The Australians want to bowl another over but the English batsmen have already started to make their way to the pavilion. Umpire Kumar Dharmasena takes the bails off and that is LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Cummins is right on the money first ball. On a good length and closer to the body of Stokes on off. He lunges forward to block.
In the channel outside off, Stokes lets it go. Cummins needs to be closer than this to make Stokes play these balls.
On the pads on a fullish length. Stokes looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg. Stokes take a run and gets off the mark with that one.

Beaten! A ripper that one. Pitched on a good length and shaped away as Denly looked to work it on the off side. Lucky not to edge that one. However, Denly will forget it quickly as he has done that throughout the innings.
Fuller around off this time, Denly strokes it straight to mid off.

FOUR! Superb timing on that one. Cummins overpitches this outside the off stump for Denly. He gets in the position and drives it handsomely through cover-point for a boundary. The cover fielder gave it a chase but came second. Denly moves into the 40s with that boundary.
A bit short outside off, cut towards the man at cover.
Fuller this time, floated outside off, pushed towards the off side.
Stokes defends this one off the front foot and onto the ground.
This time Stokes pushes this towards the cover region and takes one to get off strike.

Uppish but wide of Lyon! Denly comes down the track to Lyon again but plays this uppishly down the ground. Lyon gets down to his left but is unable to get a hand on it. The ball goes towards long off and the batters take two.
Last ball of the over, blocked out by Denly.
Length ball just outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Another one outside off by Cummins, left alone.
Cummins bowls this one again in the channel outside off, Stokes doesn't fiddle with it.
Outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to let that one through.
This time fuller and finally attacking the off pole, Stokes blocks it out back towards Cummins.
Tossed up full and wide outside off, Denly pushes this one towards point.
This time flatter on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Again flatter on middle, Denly pushes this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Shorter to Stokes by Lyon, he blocks this one out.
Another shorter one, Stokes pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Short and on middle by Lyon. Stokes blocks it out.
Full on middle and off, Denly blocks it out.
Another fuller one, pushed towards mid off by Denly.
Length ball just outside off, Denly stands tall and pushes it back towards Cummins.
Good length ball just outside the off pole, Denly opens the face of the bat and pushes this one towards cover-point.

Short of a length ball this time by Cummins, Denly goes onto the back foot and pulls it towards mid-wicket off the top half of his bat for one. Replays show he went a touch too back as his boot almost touched the wicket.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Flatter and fuller on middle, Denly lunges to push it towards mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle, Denly comes down the track to push it to the right of Lyon who gets to the ball and hits the stumps at the striker's end. Denly is safely in though.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller around off, Denly drives it left of Lyon to take a single as the ball goes towards long off.
Fuller around off, Denly drives it left of Lyon to take a single as the ball goes towards long off.
On the leg stump this time, Stokes looks to glance it down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good short ball to start of the over by Cummins, just outside the off pole, near the eye line. Denly looks to pull this one but misses it completely.
100 up for England and they are now 169/2 effectively! Good length ball on middle and leg, Denly plays this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
On middle and leg to Stokes, he flicks it towards the man at mid-wicket.
Length ball just outside off, Stokes pushes this one towards cover.

Short of a length ball outside off, Stokes pulls this one but does not time it to perfection. It goes uppishly towards square leg but way too short of the fielder, Lyon in the deep. The batters take one.
Fuller on middle and leg, driven towards mid on to end the over.
FOUR! Treat to the eyes, this shot by Stokes! Lyon tosses it up on off, Stokes comes down the track and lofts it over the fielder at mid off for a boundary.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good comeback by Lyon. He pushes this one on the off side, a touch shorter. Stokes looks to defend it off the back foot but misses.

STOKES DROPPED BY STEVEN SMITH! Lyon serves this one short and flatter outside off, Stokes goes onto the back foot and tries to cut it. It goes off the outside edge towards Steven Smith at blistering pace near his chest. Smudge tries to catch it with his fingers pointing up but it goes through them, hits his chest and then bounces out. Stokes is a man in form and Australia would want to take his wicket as quickly as possible after this dropped catch.
Outside off, left alone by Stokes.

Flatter on off, Stokes defends this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery. Good comeback by Lyon after getting hit for a boundary on the first ball. Should have got Stokes also but Smith dropped the catch.
Shortish ball pitched around off, this one is angled into the batter, Denly looks to push it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good running! Another ball on a good length, Denly looks to block but the ball takes the inside edge and goes towards deep square leg. They take a couple. Very good running between the wickets.
On middle, this one is blocked nicely.
Wanted to get to his fifty but Denly is sent back by Stokes, rightly so. Good length ball around off, Denly taps it towards point and wants a single. Stokes denies as the single was not on there.

FOUR! There is the fifty! Third one of this series, 4th overall. He gets there with a superb whip off his pads. Hazlewood dishes this full and on the leg stump line, Denly has been in the middle for too long to miss out on that one. He whips it across the line and the ball goes through to the deep square leg fence. All of his half centuries in his career have come either in the third innings or the fourth innings of a Test match. Interesting stat that one. He would want to get to his maiden century though.
Good length around off this time, he blocks it towards point.
Full and floated outside off, Stokes pushes this one towards covers and takes a single.
Floated outside off to Denly, he pushes this straight to the man at cover.
Tossed up on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on by Denly.
Flighted one on middle, Denly pushes this towards Lyon.

Close but Denly survives! This one is a touch shorter by Lyon, it skids off the pitch. Denly just about gets his bat down in time and the ball hits the inside edge and then the pad. Had he missed that, he was a goner!
On the pads, Denly flicks it away towards square leg. Good over by Lyon.
BEATEN! Jaffa from Hazlewood! This is on a length outside off, it shapes a bit away with the angle. Stokes looks to fend at it but it goes past the outside edge.
Outside off, this time Stokes chooses to leave this one alone.
Another one outside off, Stokes does not fiddle with it.
Fuller and outside off, Stokes looks to go for the stylish cover drive but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid off.
Short of a length on off, Stokes goes onto his back foot, gets on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep square leg for a single.
Solid defense by Denly off the back foot. He pushes this one towards mid off.
Short of a length on off, Stokes blocks it out.

IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! Tossed up by Lyon on middle and off, Stokes gets down on one knee and goes for the slog sweep but top edges it. It skies towards deep mid-wicket but there is no one down there and it falls safe. The batters take three while the fielders do the mopping up job.
Full and floated on off, Denly pushes this one towards mid off.
Denly comes down the track and pushes this one towards mid off. He looks for a single but is sent back by Stokes.
A touch short, pushed to point by Denly.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the pads of Stokes, he pushes it towards mid on off the back foot.
A very late call by Umpire Erasmus and it is a NO BALL! Length ball on middle and off, Stokes pushes this back towards the bowler.
Full and on the pads, pushed towards square leg.
Another one on the pads, helped to mid-wicket.
Full this time wide outside off, Stokes leans forward and drives it towards cover for a three. Great shot this one, shows the confidence of Stokes.
Short of a length on middle, Denly pulls this one towards deep backward square leg and takes a single.
This time a bumper to Stokes, he too pulls it but in front of square leg and takes a single to retain strike.
Tossed up on the off pole line by Lyon, it pitches and straightens. Stokes gets his bat down in time and blocks it with the outer half of his bat as the ball rolls towards the off side.
Stokes has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

FOUR! Poor fielding from Labuschagne here! This is tossed up outside off, Stokes pushes this towards cover. Labuschagne from point runs to his left, dives but lets the ball through from underneath him. There is no protection in the deep and it crosses the fence.

SIX! What a shot by Stokes! This one is tossed up on middle and off, Stokes gets down on one knee and properly slog sweeps it over mid-wicket. Umpire Dharmasena gets it checked upstairs before raising both his hands. This takes the lead over 200 for the hosts and they will be relieved to get there with still 8 wickets in hand.
Stokes has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads, Stokes pushes this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single to retain strike.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Stokes.
BEATEN! Stokes goes to play this one towards the off side but is beaten by the away movement as the ball goes past his outside edge.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball on middle and leg, Stokes looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.

Loud appeal by the Australians but denied by umpire Erasmus! This looks plumb to the naked eye but let's see. This is pitched just outside off, it comes back in with the angle. Denly looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the front pad. Marsh along with his teammates put in a loud appeal but the umpire has denied it. Tim Paine has a long chat with his bowler but decides against the review. Now with 2 reviews in hand, they might as well should have gone for it. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge confirms no bat. Ball Tracker now comes in and shows THREE REDS! Australia have missed a trick here as Denly is going good and it looks like luck is on his side too.
Flatter around middle, blocked nicely by Stokes.
Flighted ball on the pads, Stokes works it through mid-wicket. He wants two straightaway but decides against it seeing the rushing fielder. Just one added to the scoreboard.
Flighted on off this time, Denly pushes it back to the bowler.
Another solid block from Denly to this flatter delivery on the off side.
Quicker and fuller, pushed towards mid on.
Quicker one again, Denly looks to block but misses to get hit on the pads.

FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Stokes goes to push at it towards cover but it goes off the outer half towards backward point as the ball races to the fence. The 50-run stand is up with this boundary between Stokes and Denly.
Full and on the pads, Stokes pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Good length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Stokes.
Another one outside off, Stokes gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.
Stokes gets onto the back foot to this length ball, pushes it towards cover with soft hands and takes a single.
Full and floated outside off, blocked out by Stokes.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes pushes this towards cover.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
On the pads, Stokes pushes this towards mid on for a single.
Denly has defended this one off the back foot.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover-point.
Fuller one around off, driven straight to mid off.

Bouncer! Was that off the pads? No, the umpire gives it as runs. Stokes goes to pull it but gets a bottom edge onto the pads. The ball balloons towards short fine leg but Paine can't get there. They take a single.
On the pads, tucked towards mid on.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide. Denly goes back and bisects the cover and point fielder with his cut to get a boundary. Too shot that one.
Good length on middle, worked towards square leg for a run.
Fuller this time, pushed towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Darts one on the pads to Denly. He glances it fine down the leg side and the ball races to the fence. No chance for the deep square leg fielder there.
Flatter around off, blocked by coming forward.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter, pushed back to the point fielder.
Uppish but wide of Labuschagne. Flighted ball on off, Denly pushes it to the left of Marnus who dives to his left but can't catch that. Mid off stops and no runs taken.

FOUR! Up and over the mid off fielder. This time Denly gets to the pitch of the ball to loft it over the mid off fielder. For one moment, Denly would've had his heart in his mouth seeing the mid off fielder leaping to take the catch but this was over his attempt.
Starts with one outside off, Stokes lets it be.

Huge appeal for LBW! The umpire is unmoved. Australia do not opt for the review again. Hazlewood hurls in a good length ball around leg and takes it away with the angle. Stokes walks across the stumps in his attempt to flick it on the leg side. But Stokes misses and is rapped on the pads. They put in an unsuccessful appeal and then Tim decides not to take the DRS again. This time it's a fair call by the Aussie skipper. The Ball Tracker shows that this one is missing the off pole.
Fuller ball, pushed towards the off side.
Good length ball around off, Stokes taps it through point to get three. Cameron Bancroft, the substitute, hares after the ball and saves a run.
Fuller one around off, driven straight to mid off.
Outside off, left alone by Denly this time. A good leave as he had covered his stumps.
Marnus dishes a full toss on middle, Stokes pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Flighted one on middle, pushed towards the off side.
Another ball around off, another block towards the off side by Denly.
Flighted and fuller, pushed wide of the bowler for a single through mid off.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

Appeal but not sure if that was for a catch. It has pitched way outside off on the rough and turns into the batter. Stokes looks to reverse sweep but plays all over the ball. The Ball Tracker arrives to show that this was missing the stumps by quite a big margin. Another good call not to refer it.
Good leave that one! On a length this ball, pitched around off and came into the batter. Denly covered the stumps and shouldered arms.
Back of a length ball on middle, blocked back to the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length around off, tapped towards point.
Fuller this time, pushed towards mid off.
Fuller around off this time, Denly is solid with his block again.
Flat and on the off pole, blocked out by Stokes.

Through the gate! Labuschagne tosses this one up nicely outside off. It pitches on the rough and turns back in sharply. Stokes looks to push it towards mid off but it goes between his bat and pad, missing the off pole. Paine too is unable to collect it and it goes towards fine leg as the batters take two.
